44#define version_greater(edid, maj, min) \
45 (((edid)->version > (maj)) || \
46 ((edid)->version == (maj) && (edid)->revision > (min)))

48#define EDID_EST_TIMINGS 16
49#define EDID_STD_TIMINGS 8
50#define EDID_DETAILED_TIMINGS 4
51
52/*
53 * EDID blocks out in the wild have a variety of bugs, try to collect
54 * them here (note that userspace may work around broken monitors first,
55 * but fixes should make their way here so that the kernel "just works"
56 * on as many displays as possible).
57 */
58
59/* First detailed mode wrong, use largest 60Hz mode */
60#define EDID_QUIRK_PREFER_LARGE_60 (1 << 0)
61/* Reported 135MHz pixel clock is too high, needs adjustment */
62#define EDID_QUIRK_135_CLOCK_TOO_HIGH (1 << 1)
63/* Prefer the largest mode at 75 Hz */
64#define EDID_QUIRK_PREFER_LARGE_75 (1 << 2)
65/* Detail timing is in cm not mm */
66#define EDID_QUIRK_DETAILED_IN_CM (1 << 3)
67/* Detailed timing descriptors have bogus size values, so just take the
68 * maximum size and use that.
69 */
70#define EDID_QUIRK_DETAILED_USE_MAXIMUM_SIZE (1 << 4)
71/* Monitor forgot to set the first detailed is preferred bit. */
72#define EDID_QUIRK_FIRST_DETAILED_PREFERRED (1 << 5)
73/* use +hsync +vsync for detailed mode */
74#define EDID_QUIRK_DETAILED_SYNC_PP (1 << 6)
75/* Force reduced-blanking timings for detailed modes */
76#define EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_REDUCED_BLANKING (1 << 7)
77/* Force 8bpc */
78#define EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_8BPC (1 << 8)
79/* Force 12bpc */
80#define EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_12BPC (1 << 9)
81/* Force 6bpc */
82#define EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_6BPC (1 << 10)
83/* Force 10bpc */
84#define EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_10BPC (1 << 11)
85
86struct detailed_mode_closure {
87 struct drm_connector *connector;
88 struct edid *edid;
89 bool preferred;
90 u32 quirks;
91 int modes;
92};

97#define LEVEL_CVT 3

1261/*** DDC fetch and block validation ***/
1262
1263static const u8 edid_header[] = {
1264 0x00, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0x00
1265};
1266
1267/**
1268 * drm_edid_header_is_valid - sanity check the header of the base EDID block
1269 * @raw_edid: pointer to raw base EDID block
1270 *
1271 * Sanity check the header of the base EDID block.
1272 *
1273 * Return: 8 if the header is perfect, down to 0 if it's totally wrong.
1274 */
1275int drm_edid_header_is_valid(const u8 *raw_edid)
1276{
1277 int i, score = 0;
1278
1279 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(edid_header); i++)
1280 if (raw_edid[i] == edid_header[i])
1281 score++;
1282
1283 return score;
1284}
1285EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_edid_header_is_valid);
1286
1287static int edid_fixup __read_mostly = 6;
1288module_param_named(edid_fixup, edid_fixup, int, 0400);
1289MODULE_PARM_DESC(edid_fixup,
1290 "Minimum number of valid EDID header bytes (0-8, default 6)");
1291
1292static void drm_get_displayid(struct drm_connector *connector,
1293 struct edid *edid);
1294
1295static int drm_edid_block_checksum(const u8 *raw_edid)
1296{
1297 int i;
1298 u8 csum = 0;
1299 for (i = 0; i < EDID_LENGTH; i++)
1300 csum += raw_edid[i];
1301
1302 return csum;
1303}
1304
1305static bool drm_edid_is_zero(const u8 *in_edid, int length)
1306{
1307 if (memchr_inv(in_edid, 0, length))
1308 return false;
1309
1310 return true;
1311}
1312
1313/**
1314 * drm_edid_block_valid - Sanity check the EDID block (base or extension)
1315 * @raw_edid: pointer to raw EDID block
1316 * @block: type of block to validate (0 for base, extension otherwise)
1317 * @print_bad_edid: if true, dump bad EDID blocks to the console
1318 * @edid_corrupt: if true, the header or checksum is invalid
1319 *
1320 * Validate a base or extension EDID block and optionally dump bad blocks to
1321 * the console.
1322 *
1323 * Return: True if the block is valid, false otherwise.
1324 */
1325bool drm_edid_block_valid(u8 *raw_edid, int block, bool print_bad_edid,
1326 bool *edid_corrupt)
1327{
1328 u8 csum;
1329 struct edid *edid = (struct edid *)raw_edid;
1330
1331 if (WARN_ON(!raw_edid))
1332 return false;
1333
1334 if (edid_fixup > 8 || edid_fixup < 0)
1335 edid_fixup = 6;
1336
1337 if (block == 0) {
1338 int score = drm_edid_header_is_valid(raw_edid);
1339 if (score == 8) {
1340 if (edid_corrupt)
1341 *edid_corrupt = false;
1342 } else if (score >= edid_fixup) {
1343 /* Displayport Link CTS Core 1.2 rev1.1 test 4.2.2.6
1344 * The corrupt flag needs to be set here otherwise, the
1345 * fix-up code here will correct the problem, the
1346 * checksum is correct and the test fails
1347 */
1348 if (edid_corrupt)
1349 *edid_corrupt = true;
1350 DRM_DEBUG("Fixing EDID header, your hardware may be failing\n");
1351 memcpy(raw_edid, edid_header, sizeof(edid_header));
1352 } else {
1353 if (edid_corrupt)
1354 *edid_corrupt = true;
1355 goto bad;
1356 }
1357 }
1358
1359 csum = drm_edid_block_checksum(raw_edid);
1360 if (csum) {
1361 if (edid_corrupt)
1362 *edid_corrupt = true;
1363
1364 /* allow CEA to slide through, switches mangle this */
1365 if (raw_edid[0] == CEA_EXT) {
1366 DRM_DEBUG("EDID checksum is invalid, remainder is %d\n", csum);
1367 DRM_DEBUG("Assuming a KVM switch modified the CEA block but left the original checksum\n");
1368 } else {
1369 if (print_bad_edid)
1370 DRM_NOTE("EDID checksum is invalid, remainder is %d\n", csum);
1371
1372 goto bad;
1373 }
1374 }
1375
1376 /* per-block-type checks */
1377 switch (raw_edid[0]) {
1378 case 0: /* base */
1379 if (edid->version != 1) {
1380 DRM_NOTE("EDID has major version %d, instead of 1\n", edid->version);
1381 goto bad;
1382 }
1383
1384 if (edid->revision > 4)
1385 DRM_DEBUG("EDID minor > 4, assuming backward compatibility\n");
1386 break;
1387
1388 default:
1389 break;
1390 }
1391
1392 return true;
1393
1394bad:
1395 if (print_bad_edid) {
1396 if (drm_edid_is_zero(raw_edid, EDID_LENGTH)) {
1397 pr_notice("EDID block is all zeroes\n");
1398 } else {
1399 pr_notice("Raw EDID:\n");
1400 print_hex_dump(KERN_NOTICE,
1401 " \t", DUMP_PREFIX_NONE, 16, 1,
1402 raw_edid, EDID_LENGTH, false);
1403 }
1404 }
1405 return false;
1406}
1407EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_edid_block_valid);
1408
1409/**
1410 * drm_edid_is_valid - sanity check EDID data
1411 * @edid: EDID data
1412 *
1413 * Sanity-check an entire EDID record (including extensions)
1414 *
1415 * Return: True if the EDID data is valid, false otherwise.
1416 */
1417bool drm_edid_is_valid(struct edid *edid)
1418{
1419 int i;
1420 u8 *raw = (u8 *)edid;
1421
1422 if (!edid)
1423 return false;
1424
1425 for (i = 0; i <= edid->extensions; i++)
1426 if (!drm_edid_block_valid(raw + i * EDID_LENGTH, i, true, NULL))
1427 return false;
1428
1429 return true;
1430}
1431EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_edid_is_valid);
1432
1433#define DDC_SEGMENT_ADDR 0x30
1434/**
1435 * drm_do_probe_ddc_edid() - get EDID information via I2C
1436 * @data: I2C device adapter
1437 * @buf: EDID data buffer to be filled
1438 * @block: 128 byte EDID block to start fetching from
1439 * @len: EDID data buffer length to fetch
1440 *
1441 * Try to fetch EDID information by calling I2C driver functions.
1442 *
1443 * Return: 0 on success or -1 on failure.
1444 */
1445static int
1446drm_do_probe_ddc_edid(void *data, u8 *buf, unsigned int block, size_t len)
1447{
1448 struct i2c_adapter *adapter = data;
1449 unsigned char start = block * EDID_LENGTH;
1450 unsigned char segment = block >> 1;
1451 unsigned char xfers = segment ? 3 : 2;
1452 int ret, retries = 5;
1453
1454 /*
1455 * The core I2C driver will automatically retry the transfer if the
1456 * adapter reports EAGAIN. However, we find that bit-banging transfers
1457 * are susceptible to errors under a heavily loaded machine and
1458 * generate spurious NAKs and timeouts. Retrying the transfer
1459 * of the individual block a few times seems to overcome this.
1460 */
1461 do {
1462 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
1463 {
1464 .addr = DDC_SEGMENT_ADDR,
1465 .flags = 0,
1466 .len = 1,
1467 .buf = &segment,
1468 }, {
1469 .addr = DDC_ADDR,
1470 .flags = 0,
1471 .len = 1,
1472 .buf = &start,
1473 }, {
1474 .addr = DDC_ADDR,
1475 .flags = I2C_M_RD,
1476 .len = len,
1477 .buf = buf,
1478 }
1479 };
1480
1481 /*
1482 * Avoid sending the segment addr to not upset non-compliant
1483 * DDC monitors.
1484 */
1485 ret = i2c_transfer(adapter, &msgs[3 - xfers], xfers);
1486
1487 if (ret == -ENXIO) {
1488 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("drm: skipping non-existent adapter %s\n",
1489 adapter->name);
1490 break;
1491 }
1492 } while (ret != xfers && --retries);
1493
1494 return ret == xfers ? 0 : -1;
1495}
1496
1497static void connector_bad_edid(struct drm_connector *connector,
1498 u8 *edid, int num_blocks)
1499{
1500 int i;
1501
1502 if (connector->bad_edid_counter++ && !(drm_debug & DRM_UT_KMS))
1503 return;
1504
1505 dev_warn(connector->dev->dev,
1506 "%s: EDID is invalid:\n",
1507 connector->name);
1508 for (i = 0; i < num_blocks; i++) {
1509 u8 *block = edid + i * EDID_LENGTH;
1510 char prefix[20];
1511
1512 if (drm_edid_is_zero(block, EDID_LENGTH))
1513 sprintf(prefix, "\t[%02x] ZERO ", i);
1514 else if (!drm_edid_block_valid(block, i, false, NULL))
1515 sprintf(prefix, "\t[%02x] BAD ", i);
1516 else
1517 sprintf(prefix, "\t[%02x] GOOD ", i);
1518
1519 print_hex_dump(KERN_WARNING,
1520 prefix, DUMP_PREFIX_NONE, 16, 1,
1521 block, EDID_LENGTH, false);
1522 }
1523}
1524
1525/**
1526 * drm_do_get_edid - get EDID data using a custom EDID block read function
1527 * @connector: connector we're probing
1528 * @get_edid_block: EDID block read function
1529 * @data: private data passed to the block read function
1530 *
1531 * When the I2C adapter connected to the DDC bus is hidden behind a device that
1532 * exposes a different interface to read EDID blocks this function can be used
1533 * to get EDID data using a custom block read function.
1534 *
1535 * As in the general case the DDC bus is accessible by the kernel at the I2C
1536 * level, drivers must make all reasonable efforts to expose it as an I2C
1537 * adapter and use drm_get_edid() instead of abusing this function.
1538 *
1539 * Return: Pointer to valid EDID or NULL if we couldn't find any.
1540 */
1541struct edid *drm_do_get_edid(struct drm_connector *connector,
1542 int (*get_edid_block)(void *data, u8 *buf, unsigned int block,
1543 size_t len),
1544 void *data)
1545{
1546 int i, j = 0, valid_extensions = 0;
1547 u8 *edid, *new;
1548
1549 if ((edid = kmalloc(EDID_LENGTH, GFP_KERNEL)) == NULL)
1550 return NULL;
1551
1552 /* base block fetch */
1553 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1554 if (get_edid_block(data, edid, 0, EDID_LENGTH))
1555 goto out;
1556 if (drm_edid_block_valid(edid, 0, false,
1557 &connector->edid_corrupt))
1558 break;
1559 if (i == 0 && drm_edid_is_zero(edid, EDID_LENGTH)) {
1560 connector->null_edid_counter++;
1561 goto carp;
1562 }
1563 }
1564 if (i == 4)
1565 goto carp;
1566
1567 /* if there's no extensions, we're done */
1568 valid_extensions = edid[0x7e];
1569 if (valid_extensions == 0)
1570 return (struct edid *)edid;
1571
1572 new = krealloc(edid, (valid_extensions + 1) * EDID_LENGTH, GFP_KERNEL);
1573 if (!new)
1574 goto out;
1575 edid = new;
1576
1577 for (j = 1; j <= edid[0x7e]; j++) {
1578 u8 *block = edid + j * EDID_LENGTH;
1579
1580 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1581 if (get_edid_block(data, block, j, EDID_LENGTH))
1582 goto out;
1583 if (drm_edid_block_valid(block, j, false, NULL))
1584 break;
1585 }
1586
1587 if (i == 4)
1588 valid_extensions--;
1589 }
1590
1591 if (valid_extensions != edid[0x7e]) {
1592 u8 *base;
1593
1594 connector_bad_edid(connector, edid, edid[0x7e] + 1);
1595
1596 edid[EDID_LENGTH-1] += edid[0x7e] - valid_extensions;
1597 edid[0x7e] = valid_extensions;
1598
1599 new = kmalloc((valid_extensions + 1) * EDID_LENGTH, GFP_KERNEL);
1600 if (!new)
1601 goto out;
1602
1603 base = new;
1604 for (i = 0; i <= edid[0x7e]; i++) {
1605 u8 *block = edid + i * EDID_LENGTH;
1606
1607 if (!drm_edid_block_valid(block, i, false, NULL))
1608 continue;
1609
1610 memcpy(base, block, EDID_LENGTH);
1611 base += EDID_LENGTH;
1612 }
1613
1614 kfree(edid);
1615 edid = new;
1616 }
1617
1618 return (struct edid *)edid;
1619
1620carp:
1621 connector_bad_edid(connector, edid, 1);
1622out:
1623 kfree(edid);
1624 return NULL;
1625}
1626EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(drm_do_get_edid);
1627
1628/**
1629 * drm_probe_ddc() - probe DDC presence
1630 * @adapter: I2C adapter to probe
1631 *
1632 * Return: True on success, false on failure.
1633 */
1634bool
1635drm_probe_ddc(struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
1636{
1637 unsigned char out;
1638
1639 return (drm_do_probe_ddc_edid(adapter, &out, 0, 1) == 0);
1640}
1641EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_probe_ddc);

1643/**
1644 * drm_get_edid - get EDID data, if available
1645 * @connector: connector we're probing
1646 * @adapter: I2C adapter to use for DDC
1647 *
1648 * Poke the given I2C channel to grab EDID data if possible. If found,
1649 * attach it to the connector.
1650 *
1651 * Return: Pointer to valid EDID or NULL if we couldn't find any.
1652 */
1653struct edid *drm_get_edid(struct drm_connector *connector,
1654 struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
1655{
1656 struct edid *edid;
1657
1658 if (connector->force == DRM_FORCE_OFF)
1659 return NULL;
1660
1661 if (connector->force == DRM_FORCE_UNSPECIFIED && !drm_probe_ddc(adapter))
1662 return NULL;
1663
1664 edid = drm_do_get_edid(connector, drm_do_probe_ddc_edid, adapter);
1665 if (edid)
1666 drm_get_displayid(connector, edid);
1667 return edid;
1668}
1669EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_get_edid);
1670
1671/**
1672 * drm_get_edid_switcheroo - get EDID data for a vga_switcheroo output
1673 * @connector: connector we're probing
1674 * @adapter: I2C adapter to use for DDC
1675 *
1676 * Wrapper around drm_get_edid() for laptops with dual GPUs using one set of
1677 * outputs. The wrapper adds the requisite vga_switcheroo calls to temporarily
1678 * switch DDC to the GPU which is retrieving EDID.
1679 *
1680 * Return: Pointer to valid EDID or %NULL if we couldn't find any.
1681 */
1682struct edid *drm_get_edid_switcheroo(struct drm_connector *connector,
1683 struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
1684{
1685 struct pci_dev *pdev = connector->dev->pdev;
1686 struct edid *edid;
1687
1688 vga_switcheroo_lock_ddc(pdev);
1689 edid = drm_get_edid(connector, adapter);
1690 vga_switcheroo_unlock_ddc(pdev);
1691
1692 return edid;
1693}
1694EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_get_edid_switcheroo);

1696/**
1697 * drm_edid_duplicate - duplicate an EDID and the extensions
1698 * @edid: EDID to duplicate
1699 *
1700 * Return: Pointer to duplicated EDID or NULL on allocation failure.
1701 */
1702struct edid *drm_edid_duplicate(const struct edid *edid)
1703{
1704 return kmemdup(edid, (edid->extensions + 1) * EDID_LENGTH, GFP_KERNEL);
1705}

1708/*** EDID parsing ***/
1709
1710/**
1711 * edid_vendor - match a string against EDID's obfuscated vendor field
1712 * @edid: EDID to match
1713 * @vendor: vendor string
1714 *
1715 * Returns true if @vendor is in @edid, false otherwise
1716 */
1717static bool edid_vendor(struct edid *edid, const char *vendor)
1718{
1719 char edid_vendor[3];
1720
1721 edid_vendor[0] = ((edid->mfg_id[0] & 0x7c) >> 2) + '@';
1722 edid_vendor[1] = (((edid->mfg_id[0] & 0x3) << 3) |
1723 ((edid->mfg_id[1] & 0xe0) >> 5)) + '@';
1724 edid_vendor[2] = (edid->mfg_id[1] & 0x1f) + '@';
1725
1726 return !strncmp(edid_vendor, vendor, 3);
1727}
1728
1729/**
1730 * edid_get_quirks - return quirk flags for a given EDID
1731 * @edid: EDID to process
1732 *
1733 * This tells subsequent routines what fixes they need to apply.
1734 */
1735static u32 edid_get_quirks(struct edid *edid)
1736{
1737 const struct edid_quirk *quirk;
1738 int i;
1739
1740 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(edid_quirk_list); i++) {
1741 quirk = &edid_quirk_list[i];
1742
1743 if (edid_vendor(edid, quirk->vendor) &&
1744 (EDID_PRODUCT_ID(edid) == quirk->product_id))
1745 return quirk->quirks;
1746 }
1747
1748 return 0;
1749}
1750
1751#define MODE_SIZE(m) ((m)->hdisplay * (m)->vdisplay)
1752#define MODE_REFRESH_DIFF(c,t) (abs((c) - (t)))
1753
1754/**
1755 * edid_fixup_preferred - set preferred modes based on quirk list
1756 * @connector: has mode list to fix up
1757 * @quirks: quirks list
1758 *
1759 * Walk the mode list for @connector, clearing the preferred status
1760 * on existing modes and setting it anew for the right mode ala @quirks.
1761 */
1762static void edid_fixup_preferred(struct drm_connector *connector,
1763 u32 quirks)
1764{
1765 struct drm_display_mode *t, *cur_mode, *preferred_mode;
1766 int target_refresh = 0;
1767 int cur_vrefresh, preferred_vrefresh;
1768
1769 if (list_empty(&connector->probed_modes))
1770 return;
1771
1772 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_PREFER_LARGE_60)
1773 target_refresh = 60;
1774 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_PREFER_LARGE_75)
1775 target_refresh = 75;
1776
1777 preferred_mode = list_first_entry(&connector->probed_modes,
1778 struct drm_display_mode, head);
1779
1780 list_for_each_entry_safe(cur_mode, t, &connector->probed_modes, head) {
1781 cur_mode->type &= ~DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;
1782
1783 if (cur_mode == preferred_mode)
1784 continue;
1785
1786 /* Largest mode is preferred */
1787 if (MODE_SIZE(cur_mode) > MODE_SIZE(preferred_mode))
1788 preferred_mode = cur_mode;
1789
1790 cur_vrefresh = cur_mode->vrefresh ?
1791 cur_mode->vrefresh : drm_mode_vrefresh(cur_mode);
1792 preferred_vrefresh = preferred_mode->vrefresh ?
1793 preferred_mode->vrefresh : drm_mode_vrefresh(preferred_mode);
1794 /* At a given size, try to get closest to target refresh */
1795 if ((MODE_SIZE(cur_mode) == MODE_SIZE(preferred_mode)) &&
1796 MODE_REFRESH_DIFF(cur_vrefresh, target_refresh) <
1797 MODE_REFRESH_DIFF(preferred_vrefresh, target_refresh)) {
1798 preferred_mode = cur_mode;
1799 }
1800 }
1801
1802 preferred_mode->type |= DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;
1803}
1804
1805static bool
1806mode_is_rb(const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
1807{
1808 return (mode->htotal - mode->hdisplay == 160) &&
1809 (mode->hsync_end - mode->hdisplay == 80) &&
1810 (mode->hsync_end - mode->hsync_start == 32) &&
1811 (mode->vsync_start - mode->vdisplay == 3);
1812}
1813
1814/*
1815 * drm_mode_find_dmt - Create a copy of a mode if present in DMT
1816 * @dev: Device to duplicate against
1817 * @hsize: Mode width
1818 * @vsize: Mode height
1819 * @fresh: Mode refresh rate
1820 * @rb: Mode reduced-blanking-ness
1821 *
1822 * Walk the DMT mode list looking for a match for the given parameters.
1823 *
1824 * Return: A newly allocated copy of the mode, or NULL if not found.
1825 */
1826struct drm_display_mode *drm_mode_find_dmt(struct drm_device *dev,
1827 int hsize, int vsize, int fresh,
1828 bool rb)
1829{
1830 int i;
1831
1832 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(drm_dmt_modes); i++) {
1833 const struct drm_display_mode *ptr = &drm_dmt_modes[i];
1834 if (hsize != ptr->hdisplay)
1835 continue;
1836 if (vsize != ptr->vdisplay)
1837 continue;
1838 if (fresh != drm_mode_vrefresh(ptr))
1839 continue;
1840 if (rb != mode_is_rb(ptr))
1841 continue;
1842
1843 return drm_mode_duplicate(dev, ptr);
1844 }
1845
1846 return NULL;
1847}
1848EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_mode_find_dmt);
1849
1850typedef void detailed_cb(struct detailed_timing *timing, void *closure);
1851
1852static void
1853cea_for_each_detailed_block(u8 *ext, detailed_cb *cb, void *closure)
1854{
1855 int i, n = 0;
1856 u8 d = ext[0x02];
1857 u8 *det_base = ext + d;
1858
1859 n = (127 - d) / 18;
1860 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
1861 cb((struct detailed_timing *)(det_base + 18 * i), closure);
1862}
1863
1864static void
1865vtb_for_each_detailed_block(u8 *ext, detailed_cb *cb, void *closure)
1866{
1867 unsigned int i, n = min((int)ext[0x02], 6);
1868 u8 *det_base = ext + 5;
1869
1870 if (ext[0x01] != 1)
1871 return; /* unknown version */
1872
1873 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
1874 cb((struct detailed_timing *)(det_base + 18 * i), closure);
1875}
1876
1877static void
1878drm_for_each_detailed_block(u8 *raw_edid, detailed_cb *cb, void *closure)
1879{
1880 int i;
1881 struct edid *edid = (struct edid *)raw_edid;
1882
1883 if (edid == NULL)
1884 return;
1885
1886 for (i = 0; i < EDID_DETAILED_TIMINGS; i++)
1887 cb(&(edid->detailed_timings[i]), closure);
1888
1889 for (i = 1; i <= raw_edid[0x7e]; i++) {
1890 u8 *ext = raw_edid + (i * EDID_LENGTH);
1891 switch (*ext) {
1892 case CEA_EXT:
1893 cea_for_each_detailed_block(ext, cb, closure);
1894 break;
1895 case VTB_EXT:
1896 vtb_for_each_detailed_block(ext, cb, closure);
1897 break;
1898 default:
1899 break;
1900 }
1901 }
1902}
1903
1904static void
1905is_rb(struct detailed_timing *t, void *data)
1906{
1907 u8 *r = (u8 *)t;
1908 if (r[3] == EDID_DETAIL_MONITOR_RANGE)
1909 if (r[15] & 0x10)
1910 *(bool *)data = true;
1911}
1912
1913/* EDID 1.4 defines this explicitly. For EDID 1.3, we guess, badly. */
1914static bool
1915drm_monitor_supports_rb(struct edid *edid)
1916{
1917 if (edid->revision >= 4) {
1918 bool ret = false;
1919 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, is_rb, &ret);
1920 return ret;
1921 }
1922
1923 return ((edid->input & DRM_EDID_INPUT_DIGITAL) != 0);
1924}
1925
1926static void
1927find_gtf2(struct detailed_timing *t, void *data)
1928{
1929 u8 *r = (u8 *)t;
1930 if (r[3] == EDID_DETAIL_MONITOR_RANGE && r[10] == 0x02)
1931 *(u8 **)data = r;
1932}
1933
1934/* Secondary GTF curve kicks in above some break frequency */
1935static int
1936drm_gtf2_hbreak(struct edid *edid)
1937{
1938 u8 *r = NULL;
1939 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, find_gtf2, &r);
1940 return r ? (r[12] * 2) : 0;
1941}
1942
1943static int
1944drm_gtf2_2c(struct edid *edid)
1945{
1946 u8 *r = NULL;
1947 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, find_gtf2, &r);
1948 return r ? r[13] : 0;
1949}
1950
1951static int
1952drm_gtf2_m(struct edid *edid)
1953{
1954 u8 *r = NULL;
1955 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, find_gtf2, &r);
1956 return r ? (r[15] << 8) + r[14] : 0;
1957}
1958
1959static int
1960drm_gtf2_k(struct edid *edid)
1961{
1962 u8 *r = NULL;
1963 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, find_gtf2, &r);
1964 return r ? r[16] : 0;
1965}
1966
1967static int
1968drm_gtf2_2j(struct edid *edid)
1969{
1970 u8 *r = NULL;
1971 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, find_gtf2, &r);
1972 return r ? r[17] : 0;
1973}

1975/**
1976 * standard_timing_level - get std. timing level(CVT/GTF/DMT)
1977 * @edid: EDID block to scan
1978 */
1979static int standard_timing_level(struct edid *edid)
1980{
1981 if (edid->revision >= 2) {
1982 if (edid->revision >= 4 && (edid->features & DRM_EDID_FEATURE_DEFAULT_GTF))
1983 return LEVEL_CVT;
1984 if (drm_gtf2_hbreak(edid))
1985 return LEVEL_GTF2;
1986 return LEVEL_GTF;
1987 }
1988 return LEVEL_DMT;
1989}
1990
1991/*
1992 * 0 is reserved. The spec says 0x01 fill for unused timings. Some old
1993 * monitors fill with ascii space (0x20) instead.
1994 */
1995static int
1996bad_std_timing(u8 a, u8 b)
1997{
1998 return (a == 0x00 && b == 0x00) ||
1999 (a == 0x01 && b == 0x01) ||
2000 (a == 0x20 && b == 0x20);
2001}
2002
2003/**
2004 * drm_mode_std - convert standard mode info (width, height, refresh) into mode
2005 * @connector: connector of for the EDID block
2006 * @edid: EDID block to scan
2007 * @t: standard timing params
2008 *
2009 * Take the standard timing params (in this case width, aspect, and refresh)
2010 * and convert them into a real mode using CVT/GTF/DMT.
2011 */
2012static struct drm_display_mode *
2013drm_mode_std(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid,
2014 struct std_timing *t)
2015{
2016 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
2017 struct drm_display_mode *m, *mode = NULL;
2018 int hsize, vsize;
2019 int vrefresh_rate;
2020 unsigned aspect_ratio = (t->vfreq_aspect & EDID_TIMING_ASPECT_MASK)
2021 >> EDID_TIMING_ASPECT_SHIFT;
2022 unsigned vfreq = (t->vfreq_aspect & EDID_TIMING_VFREQ_MASK)
2023 >> EDID_TIMING_VFREQ_SHIFT;
2024 int timing_level = standard_timing_level(edid);
2025
2026 if (bad_std_timing(t->hsize, t->vfreq_aspect))
2027 return NULL;
2028
2029 /* According to the EDID spec, the hdisplay = hsize * 8 + 248 */
2030 hsize = t->hsize * 8 + 248;
2031 /* vrefresh_rate = vfreq + 60 */
2032 vrefresh_rate = vfreq + 60;
2033 /* the vdisplay is calculated based on the aspect ratio */
2034 if (aspect_ratio == 0) {
2035 if (edid->revision < 3)
2036 vsize = hsize;
2037 else
2038 vsize = (hsize * 10) / 16;
2039 } else if (aspect_ratio == 1)
2040 vsize = (hsize * 3) / 4;
2041 else if (aspect_ratio == 2)
2042 vsize = (hsize * 4) / 5;
2043 else
2044 vsize = (hsize * 9) / 16;
2045
2046 /* HDTV hack, part 1 */
2047 if (vrefresh_rate == 60 &&
2048 ((hsize == 1360 && vsize == 765) ||
2049 (hsize == 1368 && vsize == 769))) {
2050 hsize = 1366;
2051 vsize = 768;
2052 }
2053
2054 /*
2055 * If this connector already has a mode for this size and refresh
2056 * rate (because it came from detailed or CVT info), use that
2057 * instead. This way we don't have to guess at interlace or
2058 * reduced blanking.
2059 */
2060 list_for_each_entry(m, &connector->probed_modes, head)
2061 if (m->hdisplay == hsize && m->vdisplay == vsize &&
2062 drm_mode_vrefresh(m) == vrefresh_rate)
2063 return NULL;
2064
2065 /* HDTV hack, part 2 */
2066 if (hsize == 1366 && vsize == 768 && vrefresh_rate == 60) {
2067 mode = drm_cvt_mode(dev, 1366, 768, vrefresh_rate, 0, 0,
2068 false);
2069 mode->hdisplay = 1366;
2070 mode->hsync_start = mode->hsync_start - 1;
2071 mode->hsync_end = mode->hsync_end - 1;
2072 return mode;
2073 }
2074
2075 /* check whether it can be found in default mode table */
2076 if (drm_monitor_supports_rb(edid)) {
2077 mode = drm_mode_find_dmt(dev, hsize, vsize, vrefresh_rate,
2078 true);
2079 if (mode)
2080 return mode;
2081 }
2082 mode = drm_mode_find_dmt(dev, hsize, vsize, vrefresh_rate, false);
2083 if (mode)
2084 return mode;
2085
2086 /* okay, generate it */
2087 switch (timing_level) {
2088 case LEVEL_DMT:
2089 break;
2090 case LEVEL_GTF:
2091 mode = drm_gtf_mode(dev, hsize, vsize, vrefresh_rate, 0, 0);
2092 break;
2093 case LEVEL_GTF2:
2094 /*
2095 * This is potentially wrong if there's ever a monitor with
2096 * more than one ranges section, each claiming a different
2097 * secondary GTF curve. Please don't do that.
2098 */
2099 mode = drm_gtf_mode(dev, hsize, vsize, vrefresh_rate, 0, 0);
2100 if (!mode)
2101 return NULL;
2102 if (drm_mode_hsync(mode) > drm_gtf2_hbreak(edid)) {
2103 drm_mode_destroy(dev, mode);
2104 mode = drm_gtf_mode_complex(dev, hsize, vsize,
2105 vrefresh_rate, 0, 0,
2106 drm_gtf2_m(edid),
2107 drm_gtf2_2c(edid),
2108 drm_gtf2_k(edid),
2109 drm_gtf2_2j(edid));
2110 }
2111 break;
2112 case LEVEL_CVT:
2113 mode = drm_cvt_mode(dev, hsize, vsize, vrefresh_rate, 0, 0,
2114 false);
2115 break;
2116 }
2117 return mode;
2118}
2119
2120/*
2121 * EDID is delightfully ambiguous about how interlaced modes are to be
2122 * encoded. Our internal representation is of frame height, but some
2123 * HDTV detailed timings are encoded as field height.
2124 *
2125 * The format list here is from CEA, in frame size. Technically we
2126 * should be checking refresh rate too. Whatever.
2127 */
2128static void
2129drm_mode_do_interlace_quirk(struct drm_display_mode *mode,
2130 struct detailed_pixel_timing *pt)
2131{
2132 int i;
2133 static const struct {
2134 int w, h;
2135 } cea_interlaced[] = {
2136 { 1920, 1080 },
2137 { 720, 480 },
2138 { 1440, 480 },
2139 { 2880, 480 },
2140 { 720, 576 },
2141 { 1440, 576 },
2142 { 2880, 576 },
2143 };
2144
2145 if (!(pt->misc & DRM_EDID_PT_INTERLACED))
2146 return;
2147
2148 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(cea_interlaced); i++) {
2149 if ((mode->hdisplay == cea_interlaced[i].w) &&
2150 (mode->vdisplay == cea_interlaced[i].h / 2)) {
2151 mode->vdisplay *= 2;
2152 mode->vsync_start *= 2;
2153 mode->vsync_end *= 2;
2154 mode->vtotal *= 2;
2155 mode->vtotal |= 1;
2156 }
2157 }
2158
2159 mode->flags |= DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE;
2160}
2161
2162/**
2163 * drm_mode_detailed - create a new mode from an EDID detailed timing section
2164 * @dev: DRM device (needed to create new mode)
2165 * @edid: EDID block
2166 * @timing: EDID detailed timing info
2167 * @quirks: quirks to apply
2168 *
2169 * An EDID detailed timing block contains enough info for us to create and
2170 * return a new struct drm_display_mode.
2171 */
2172static struct drm_display_mode *drm_mode_detailed(struct drm_device *dev,
2173 struct edid *edid,
2174 struct detailed_timing *timing,
2175 u32 quirks)
2176{
2177 struct drm_display_mode *mode;
2178 struct detailed_pixel_timing *pt = &timing->data.pixel_data;
2179 unsigned hactive = (pt->hactive_hblank_hi & 0xf0) << 4 | pt->hactive_lo;
2180 unsigned vactive = (pt->vactive_vblank_hi & 0xf0) << 4 | pt->vactive_lo;
2181 unsigned hblank = (pt->hactive_hblank_hi & 0xf) << 8 | pt->hblank_lo;
2182 unsigned vblank = (pt->vactive_vblank_hi & 0xf) << 8 | pt->vblank_lo;
2183 unsigned hsync_offset = (pt->hsync_vsync_offset_pulse_width_hi & 0xc0) << 2 | pt->hsync_offset_lo;
2184 unsigned hsync_pulse_width = (pt->hsync_vsync_offset_pulse_width_hi & 0x30) << 4 | pt->hsync_pulse_width_lo;
2185 unsigned vsync_offset = (pt->hsync_vsync_offset_pulse_width_hi & 0xc) << 2 | pt->vsync_offset_pulse_width_lo >> 4;
2186 unsigned vsync_pulse_width = (pt->hsync_vsync_offset_pulse_width_hi & 0x3) << 4 | (pt->vsync_offset_pulse_width_lo & 0xf);
2187
2188 /* ignore tiny modes */
2189 if (hactive < 64 || vactive < 64)
2190 return NULL;
2191
2192 if (pt->misc & DRM_EDID_PT_STEREO) {
2193 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("stereo mode not supported\n");
2194 return NULL;
2195 }
2196 if (!(pt->misc & DRM_EDID_PT_SEPARATE_SYNC)) {
2197 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("composite sync not supported\n");
2198 }
2199
2200 /* it is incorrect if hsync/vsync width is zero */
2201 if (!hsync_pulse_width || !vsync_pulse_width) {
2202 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Incorrect Detailed timing. "
2203 "Wrong Hsync/Vsync pulse width\n");
2204 return NULL;
2205 }
2206
2207 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_REDUCED_BLANKING) {
2208 mode = drm_cvt_mode(dev, hactive, vactive, 60, true, false, false);
2209 if (!mode)
2210 return NULL;
2211
2212 goto set_size;
2213 }
2214
2215 mode = drm_mode_create(dev);
2216 if (!mode)
2217 return NULL;
2218
2219 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_135_CLOCK_TOO_HIGH)
2220 timing->pixel_clock = cpu_to_le16(1088);
2221
2222 mode->clock = le16_to_cpu(timing->pixel_clock) * 10;
2223
2224 mode->hdisplay = hactive;
2225 mode->hsync_start = mode->hdisplay + hsync_offset;
2226 mode->hsync_end = mode->hsync_start + hsync_pulse_width;
2227 mode->htotal = mode->hdisplay + hblank;
2228
2229 mode->vdisplay = vactive;
2230 mode->vsync_start = mode->vdisplay + vsync_offset;
2231 mode->vsync_end = mode->vsync_start + vsync_pulse_width;
2232 mode->vtotal = mode->vdisplay + vblank;
2233
2234 /* Some EDIDs have bogus h/vtotal values */
2235 if (mode->hsync_end > mode->htotal)
2236 mode->htotal = mode->hsync_end + 1;
2237 if (mode->vsync_end > mode->vtotal)
2238 mode->vtotal = mode->vsync_end + 1;
2239
2240 drm_mode_do_interlace_quirk(mode, pt);
2241
2242 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_DETAILED_SYNC_PP) {
2243 pt->misc |= DRM_EDID_PT_HSYNC_POSITIVE | DRM_EDID_PT_VSYNC_POSITIVE;
2244 }
2245
2246 mode->flags |= (pt->misc & DRM_EDID_PT_HSYNC_POSITIVE) ?
2247 DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC : DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
2248 mode->flags |= (pt->misc & DRM_EDID_PT_VSYNC_POSITIVE) ?
2249 DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC : DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
2250
2251set_size:
2252 mode->width_mm = pt->width_mm_lo | (pt->width_height_mm_hi & 0xf0) << 4;
2253 mode->height_mm = pt->height_mm_lo | (pt->width_height_mm_hi & 0xf) << 8;
2254
2255 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_DETAILED_IN_CM) {
2256 mode->width_mm *= 10;
2257 mode->height_mm *= 10;
2258 }
2259
2260 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_DETAILED_USE_MAXIMUM_SIZE) {
2261 mode->width_mm = edid->width_cm * 10;
2262 mode->height_mm = edid->height_cm * 10;
2263 }
2264
2265 mode->type = DRM_MODE_TYPE_DRIVER;
2266 mode->vrefresh = drm_mode_vrefresh(mode);
2267 drm_mode_set_name(mode);
2268
2269 return mode;
2270}
2271
2272static bool
2273mode_in_hsync_range(const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
2274 struct edid *edid, u8 *t)
2275{
2276 int hsync, hmin, hmax;
2277
2278 hmin = t[7];
2279 if (edid->revision >= 4)
2280 hmin += ((t[4] & 0x04) ? 255 : 0);
2281 hmax = t[8];
2282 if (edid->revision >= 4)
2283 hmax += ((t[4] & 0x08) ? 255 : 0);
2284 hsync = drm_mode_hsync(mode);
2285
2286 return (hsync <= hmax && hsync >= hmin);
2287}
2288
2289static bool
2290mode_in_vsync_range(const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
2291 struct edid *edid, u8 *t)
2292{
2293 int vsync, vmin, vmax;
2294
2295 vmin = t[5];
2296 if (edid->revision >= 4)
2297 vmin += ((t[4] & 0x01) ? 255 : 0);
2298 vmax = t[6];
2299 if (edid->revision >= 4)
2300 vmax += ((t[4] & 0x02) ? 255 : 0);
2301 vsync = drm_mode_vrefresh(mode);
2302
2303 return (vsync <= vmax && vsync >= vmin);
2304}
2305
2306static u32
2307range_pixel_clock(struct edid *edid, u8 *t)
2308{
2309 /* unspecified */
2310 if (t[9] == 0 || t[9] == 255)
2311 return 0;
2312
2313 /* 1.4 with CVT support gives us real precision, yay */
2314 if (edid->revision >= 4 && t[10] == 0x04)
2315 return (t[9] * 10000) - ((t[12] >> 2) * 250);
2316
2317 /* 1.3 is pathetic, so fuzz up a bit */
2318 return t[9] * 10000 + 5001;
2319}
2320
2321static bool
2322mode_in_range(const struct drm_display_mode *mode, struct edid *edid,
2323 struct detailed_timing *timing)
2324{
2325 u32 max_clock;
2326 u8 *t = (u8 *)timing;
2327
2328 if (!mode_in_hsync_range(mode, edid, t))
2329 return false;
2330
2331 if (!mode_in_vsync_range(mode, edid, t))
2332 return false;
2333
2334 if ((max_clock = range_pixel_clock(edid, t)))
2335 if (mode->clock > max_clock)
2336 return false;
2337
2338 /* 1.4 max horizontal check */
2339 if (edid->revision >= 4 && t[10] == 0x04)
2340 if (t[13] && mode->hdisplay > 8 * (t[13] + (256 * (t[12]&0x3))))
2341 return false;
2342
2343 if (mode_is_rb(mode) && !drm_monitor_supports_rb(edid))
2344 return false;
2345
2346 return true;
2347}
2348
2349static bool valid_inferred_mode(const struct drm_connector *connector,
2350 const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
2351{
2352 const struct drm_display_mode *m;
2353 bool ok = false;
2354
2355 list_for_each_entry(m, &connector->probed_modes, head) {
2356 if (mode->hdisplay == m->hdisplay &&
2357 mode->vdisplay == m->vdisplay &&
2358 drm_mode_vrefresh(mode) == drm_mode_vrefresh(m))
2359 return false; /* duplicated */
2360 if (mode->hdisplay <= m->hdisplay &&
2361 mode->vdisplay <= m->vdisplay)
2362 ok = true;
2363 }
2364 return ok;
2365}

2367static int
2368drm_dmt_modes_for_range(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid,
2369 struct detailed_timing *timing)
2370{
2371 int i, modes = 0;
2372 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
2373 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
2374
2375 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(drm_dmt_modes); i++) {
2376 if (mode_in_range(drm_dmt_modes + i, edid, timing) &&
2377 valid_inferred_mode(connector, drm_dmt_modes + i)) {
2378 newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, &drm_dmt_modes[i]);
2379 if (newmode) {
2380 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
2381 modes++;
2382 }
2383 }
2384 }
2385
2386 return modes;
2387}

2389/* fix up 1366x768 mode from 1368x768;
2390 * GFT/CVT can't express 1366 width which isn't dividable by 8
2391 */
2392void drm_mode_fixup_1366x768(struct drm_display_mode *mode)
2393{
2394 if (mode->hdisplay == 1368 && mode->vdisplay == 768) {
2395 mode->hdisplay = 1366;
2396 mode->hsync_start--;
2397 mode->hsync_end--;
2398 drm_mode_set_name(mode);
2399 }
2400}

2402static int
2403drm_gtf_modes_for_range(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid,
2404 struct detailed_timing *timing)
2405{
2406 int i, modes = 0;
2407 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
2408 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
2409
2410 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(extra_modes); i++) {
2411 const struct minimode *m = &extra_modes[i];
2412 newmode = drm_gtf_mode(dev, m->w, m->h, m->r, 0, 0);
2413 if (!newmode)
2414 return modes;
2415
2416 drm_mode_fixup_1366x768(newmode);
2417 if (!mode_in_range(newmode, edid, timing) ||
2418 !valid_inferred_mode(connector, newmode)) {
2419 drm_mode_destroy(dev, newmode);
2420 continue;
2421 }
2422
2423 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
2424 modes++;
2425 }
2426
2427 return modes;
2428}

2430static int
2431drm_cvt_modes_for_range(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid,
2432 struct detailed_timing *timing)
2433{
2434 int i, modes = 0;
2435 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
2436 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
2437 bool rb = drm_monitor_supports_rb(edid);
2438
2439 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(extra_modes); i++) {
2440 const struct minimode *m = &extra_modes[i];
2441 newmode = drm_cvt_mode(dev, m->w, m->h, m->r, rb, 0, 0);
2442 if (!newmode)
2443 return modes;
2444
2445 drm_mode_fixup_1366x768(newmode);
2446 if (!mode_in_range(newmode, edid, timing) ||
2447 !valid_inferred_mode(connector, newmode)) {
2448 drm_mode_destroy(dev, newmode);
2449 continue;
2450 }
2451
2452 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
2453 modes++;
2454 }

2456 return modes;

2458
2459static void
2460do_inferred_modes(struct detailed_timing *timing, void *c)
2461{
2462 struct detailed_mode_closure *closure = c;
2463 struct detailed_non_pixel *data = &timing->data.other_data;
2464 struct detailed_data_monitor_range *range = &data->data.range;
2465
2466 if (data->type != EDID_DETAIL_MONITOR_RANGE)
2467 return;
2468
2469 closure->modes += drm_dmt_modes_for_range(closure->connector,
2470 closure->edid,
2471 timing);
2472
2473 if (!version_greater(closure->edid, 1, 1))
2474 return; /* GTF not defined yet */
2475
2476 switch (range->flags) {
2477 case 0x02: /* secondary gtf, XXX could do more */
2478 case 0x00: /* default gtf */
2479 closure->modes += drm_gtf_modes_for_range(closure->connector,
2480 closure->edid,
2481 timing);
2482 break;
2483 case 0x04: /* cvt, only in 1.4+ */
2484 if (!version_greater(closure->edid, 1, 3))
2485 break;
2486
2487 closure->modes += drm_cvt_modes_for_range(closure->connector,
2488 closure->edid,
2489 timing);
2490 break;
2491 case 0x01: /* just the ranges, no formula */
2492 default:
2493 break;
2494 }
2495}

2497static int
2498add_inferred_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid)
2499{
2500 struct detailed_mode_closure closure = {
2501 .connector = connector,
2502 .edid = edid,
2503 };
2504
2505 if (version_greater(edid, 1, 0))
2506 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, do_inferred_modes,
2507 &closure);
2508
2509 return closure.modes;
2510}

2512static int
2513drm_est3_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, struct detailed_timing *timing)
2514{
2515 int i, j, m, modes = 0;
2516 struct drm_display_mode *mode;
2517 u8 *est = ((u8 *)timing) + 6;
2518
2519 for (i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
2520 for (j = 7; j >= 0; j--) {
2521 m = (i * 8) + (7 - j);
2522 if (m >= ARRAY_SIZE(est3_modes))
2523 break;
2524 if (est[i] & (1 << j)) {
2525 mode = drm_mode_find_dmt(connector->dev,
2526 est3_modes[m].w,
2527 est3_modes[m].h,
2528 est3_modes[m].r,
2529 est3_modes[m].rb);
2530 if (mode) {
2531 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, mode);
2532 modes++;
2533 }
2534 }
2535 }
2536 }
2537
2538 return modes;
2539}

2551/**
2552 * add_established_modes - get est. modes from EDID and add them
2553 * @connector: connector to add mode(s) to
2554 * @edid: EDID block to scan
2555 *
2556 * Each EDID block contains a bitmap of the supported "established modes" list
2557 * (defined above). Tease them out and add them to the global modes list.
2558 */
2559static int
2560add_established_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid)
2561{
2562 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
2563 unsigned long est_bits = edid->established_timings.t1 |
2564 (edid->established_timings.t2 << 8) |
2565 ((edid->established_timings.mfg_rsvd & 0x80) << 9);
2566 int i, modes = 0;
2567 struct detailed_mode_closure closure = {
2568 .connector = connector,
2569 .edid = edid,
2570 };
2571
2572 for (i = 0; i <= EDID_EST_TIMINGS; i++) {
2573 if (est_bits & (1<<i)) {
2574 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
2575 newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, &edid_est_modes[i]);
2576 if (newmode) {
2577 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
2578 modes++;
2579 }
2580 }
2581 }
2582
2583 if (version_greater(edid, 1, 0))
2584 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid,
2585 do_established_modes, &closure);
2586
2587 return modes + closure.modes;
2588}

2650
2651static int drm_cvt_modes(struct drm_connector *connector,
2652 struct detailed_timing *timing)
2653{
2654 int i, j, modes = 0;
2655 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
2656 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
2657 struct cvt_timing *cvt;
2658 const int rates[] = { 60, 85, 75, 60, 50 };
2659 const u8 empty[3] = { 0, 0, 0 };
2660
2661 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
2662 int uninitialized_var(width), height;
2663 cvt = &(timing->data.other_data.data.cvt[i]);
2664
2665 if (!memcmp(cvt->code, empty, 3))
2666 continue;
2667
2668 height = (cvt->code[0] + ((cvt->code[1] & 0xf0) << 4) + 1) * 2;
2669 switch (cvt->code[1] & 0x0c) {
2670 case 0x00:
2671 width = height * 4 / 3;
2672 break;
2673 case 0x04:
2674 width = height * 16 / 9;
2675 break;
2676 case 0x08:
2677 width = height * 16 / 10;
2678 break;
2679 case 0x0c:
2680 width = height * 15 / 9;
2681 break;
2682 }
2683
2684 for (j = 1; j < 5; j++) {
2685 if (cvt->code[2] & (1 << j)) {
2686 newmode = drm_cvt_mode(dev, width, height,
2687 rates[j], j == 0,
2688 false, false);
2689 if (newmode) {
2690 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
2691 modes++;
2692 }
2693 }
2694 }
2695 }
2696
2697 return modes;
2698}

2726static void fixup_detailed_cea_mode_clock(struct drm_display_mode *mode);
2727
2728static void
2729do_detailed_mode(struct detailed_timing *timing, void *c)
2730{
2731 struct detailed_mode_closure *closure = c;
2732 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
2733
2734 if (timing->pixel_clock) {
2735 newmode = drm_mode_detailed(closure->connector->dev,
2736 closure->edid, timing,
2737 closure->quirks);
2738 if (!newmode)
2739 return;
2740
2741 if (closure->preferred)
2742 newmode->type |= DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;
2743
2744 /*
2745 * Detailed modes are limited to 10kHz pixel clock resolution,
2746 * so fix up anything that looks like CEA/HDMI mode, but the clock
2747 * is just slightly off.
2748 */
2749 fixup_detailed_cea_mode_clock(newmode);
2750
2751 drm_mode_probed_add(closure->connector, newmode);
2752 closure->modes++;
2753 closure->preferred = 0;
2754 }
2755}

2796/*
2797 * Search EDID for CEA extension block.
2798 */
2799static u8 *drm_find_edid_extension(struct edid *edid, int ext_id)
2800{
2801 u8 *edid_ext = NULL;
2802 int i;
2803
2804 /* No EDID or EDID extensions */
2805 if (edid == NULL || edid->extensions == 0)
2806 return NULL;
2807
2808 /* Find CEA extension */
2809 for (i = 0; i < edid->extensions; i++) {
2810 edid_ext = (u8 *)edid + EDID_LENGTH * (i + 1);
2811 if (edid_ext[0] == ext_id)
2812 break;
2813 }
2814
2815 if (i == edid->extensions)
2816 return NULL;
2817
2818 return edid_ext;
2819}

2831/*
2832 * Calculate the alternate clock for the CEA mode
2833 * (60Hz vs. 59.94Hz etc.)
2834 */
2835static unsigned int
2836cea_mode_alternate_clock(const struct drm_display_mode *cea_mode)
2837{
2838 unsigned int clock = cea_mode->clock;
2839
2840 if (cea_mode->vrefresh % 6 != 0)
2841 return clock;
2842
2843 /*
2844 * edid_cea_modes contains the 59.94Hz
2845 * variant for 240 and 480 line modes,
2846 * and the 60Hz variant otherwise.
2847 */
2848 if (cea_mode->vdisplay == 240 || cea_mode->vdisplay == 480)
2849 clock = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(clock * 1001, 1000);
2850 else
2851 clock = DIV_ROUND_CLOSEST(clock * 1000, 1001);
2852
2853 return clock;
2854}
2855
2856static bool
2857cea_mode_alternate_timings(u8 vic, struct drm_display_mode *mode)
2858{
2859 /*
2860 * For certain VICs the spec allows the vertical
2861 * front porch to vary by one or two lines.
2862 *
2863 * cea_modes[] stores the variant with the shortest
2864 * vertical front porch. We can adjust the mode to
2865 * get the other variants by simply increasing the
2866 * vertical front porch length.
2867 */
2868 BUILD_BUG_ON(edid_cea_modes[8].vtotal != 262 ||
2869 edid_cea_modes[9].vtotal != 262 ||
2870 edid_cea_modes[12].vtotal != 262 ||
2871 edid_cea_modes[13].vtotal != 262 ||
2872 edid_cea_modes[23].vtotal != 312 ||
2873 edid_cea_modes[24].vtotal != 312 ||
2874 edid_cea_modes[27].vtotal != 312 ||
2875 edid_cea_modes[28].vtotal != 312);
2876
2877 if (((vic == 8 || vic == 9 ||
2878 vic == 12 || vic == 13) && mode->vtotal < 263) ||
2879 ((vic == 23 || vic == 24 ||
2880 vic == 27 || vic == 28) && mode->vtotal < 314)) {
2881 mode->vsync_start++;
2882 mode->vsync_end++;
2883 mode->vtotal++;
2884
2885 return true;
2886 }
2887
2888 return false;
2889}
2890
2891static u8 drm_match_cea_mode_clock_tolerance(const struct drm_display_mode *to_match,
2892 unsigned int clock_tolerance)
2893{
2894 u8 vic;
2895
2896 if (!to_match->clock)
2897 return 0;
2898
2899 for (vic = 1; vic < ARRAY_SIZE(edid_cea_modes); vic++) {
2900 struct drm_display_mode cea_mode = edid_cea_modes[vic];
2901 unsigned int clock1, clock2;
2902
2903 /* Check both 60Hz and 59.94Hz */
2904 clock1 = cea_mode.clock;
2905 clock2 = cea_mode_alternate_clock(&cea_mode);
2906
2907 if (abs(to_match->clock - clock1) > clock_tolerance &&
2908 abs(to_match->clock - clock2) > clock_tolerance)
2909 continue;
2910
2911 do {
2912 if (drm_mode_equal_no_clocks_no_stereo(to_match, &cea_mode))
2913 return vic;
2914 } while (cea_mode_alternate_timings(vic, &cea_mode));
2915 }
2916
2917 return 0;
2918}
2919
2920/**
2921 * drm_match_cea_mode - look for a CEA mode matching given mode
2922 * @to_match: display mode
2923 *
2924 * Return: The CEA Video ID (VIC) of the mode or 0 if it isn't a CEA-861
2925 * mode.
2926 */
2927u8 drm_match_cea_mode(const struct drm_display_mode *to_match)
2928{
2929 u8 vic;
2930
2931 if (!to_match->clock)
2932 return 0;
2933
2934 for (vic = 1; vic < ARRAY_SIZE(edid_cea_modes); vic++) {
2935 struct drm_display_mode cea_mode = edid_cea_modes[vic];
2936 unsigned int clock1, clock2;
2937
2938 /* Check both 60Hz and 59.94Hz */
2939 clock1 = cea_mode.clock;
2940 clock2 = cea_mode_alternate_clock(&cea_mode);
2941
2942 if (KHZ2PICOS(to_match->clock) != KHZ2PICOS(clock1) &&
2943 KHZ2PICOS(to_match->clock) != KHZ2PICOS(clock2))
2944 continue;
2945
2946 do {
2947 if (drm_mode_equal_no_clocks_no_stereo(to_match, &cea_mode))
2948 return vic;
2949 } while (cea_mode_alternate_timings(vic, &cea_mode));
2950 }
2951
2952 return 0;
2953}
2954EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_match_cea_mode);
2955
2956static bool drm_valid_cea_vic(u8 vic)
2957{
2958 return vic > 0 && vic < ARRAY_SIZE(edid_cea_modes);
2959}

2961/**
2962 * drm_get_cea_aspect_ratio - get the picture aspect ratio corresponding to
2963 * the input VIC from the CEA mode list
2964 * @video_code: ID given to each of the CEA modes
2965 *
2966 * Returns picture aspect ratio
2967 */
2968enum hdmi_picture_aspect drm_get_cea_aspect_ratio(const u8 video_code)
2969{
2970 return edid_cea_modes[video_code].picture_aspect_ratio;
2971}

2974/*
2975 * Calculate the alternate clock for HDMI modes (those from the HDMI vendor
2976 * specific block).
2977 *
2978 * It's almost like cea_mode_alternate_clock(), we just need to add an
2979 * exception for the VIC 4 mode (4096x2160@24Hz): no alternate clock for this
2980 * one.
2981 */
2982static unsigned int
2983hdmi_mode_alternate_clock(const struct drm_display_mode *hdmi_mode)
2984{
2985 if (hdmi_mode->vdisplay == 4096 && hdmi_mode->hdisplay == 2160)
2986 return hdmi_mode->clock;
2987
2988 return cea_mode_alternate_clock(hdmi_mode);
2989}
2990
2991static u8 drm_match_hdmi_mode_clock_tolerance(const struct drm_display_mode *to_match,
2992 unsigned int clock_tolerance)
2993{
2994 u8 vic;
2995
2996 if (!to_match->clock)
2997 return 0;
2998
2999 for (vic = 1; vic < ARRAY_SIZE(edid_4k_modes); vic++) {
3000 const struct drm_display_mode *hdmi_mode = &edid_4k_modes[vic];
3001 unsigned int clock1, clock2;
3002
3003 /* Make sure to also match alternate clocks */
3004 clock1 = hdmi_mode->clock;
3005 clock2 = hdmi_mode_alternate_clock(hdmi_mode);
3006
3007 if (abs(to_match->clock - clock1) > clock_tolerance &&
3008 abs(to_match->clock - clock2) > clock_tolerance)
3009 continue;
3010
3011 if (drm_mode_equal_no_clocks(to_match, hdmi_mode))
3012 return vic;
3013 }
3014
3015 return 0;
3016}

3018/*
3019 * drm_match_hdmi_mode - look for a HDMI mode matching given mode
3020 * @to_match: display mode
3021 *
3022 * An HDMI mode is one defined in the HDMI vendor specific block.
3023 *
3024 * Returns the HDMI Video ID (VIC) of the mode or 0 if it isn't one.
3025 */
3026static u8 drm_match_hdmi_mode(const struct drm_display_mode *to_match)
3027{
3028 u8 vic;
3029
3030 if (!to_match->clock)
3031 return 0;
3032
3033 for (vic = 1; vic < ARRAY_SIZE(edid_4k_modes); vic++) {
3034 const struct drm_display_mode *hdmi_mode = &edid_4k_modes[vic];
3035 unsigned int clock1, clock2;
3036
3037 /* Make sure to also match alternate clocks */
3038 clock1 = hdmi_mode->clock;
3039 clock2 = hdmi_mode_alternate_clock(hdmi_mode);
3040
3041 if ((KHZ2PICOS(to_match->clock) == KHZ2PICOS(clock1) ||
3042 KHZ2PICOS(to_match->clock) == KHZ2PICOS(clock2)) &&
3043 drm_mode_equal_no_clocks_no_stereo(to_match, hdmi_mode))
3044 return vic;
3045 }
3046 return 0;
3047}

3049static bool drm_valid_hdmi_vic(u8 vic)
3050{
3051 return vic > 0 && vic < ARRAY_SIZE(edid_4k_modes);
3052}
3053
3054static int
3055add_alternate_cea_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid)
3056{
3057 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
3058 struct drm_display_mode *mode, *tmp;
3059 LIST_HEAD(list);
3060 int modes = 0;
3061
3062 /* Don't add CEA modes if the CEA extension block is missing */
3063 if (!drm_find_cea_extension(edid))
3064 return 0;
3065
3066 /*
3067 * Go through all probed modes and create a new mode
3068 * with the alternate clock for certain CEA modes.
3069 */
3070 list_for_each_entry(mode, &connector->probed_modes, head) {
3071 const struct drm_display_mode *cea_mode = NULL;
3072 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
3073 u8 vic = drm_match_cea_mode(mode);
3074 unsigned int clock1, clock2;
3075
3076 if (drm_valid_cea_vic(vic)) {
3077 cea_mode = &edid_cea_modes[vic];
3078 clock2 = cea_mode_alternate_clock(cea_mode);
3079 } else {
3080 vic = drm_match_hdmi_mode(mode);
3081 if (drm_valid_hdmi_vic(vic)) {
3082 cea_mode = &edid_4k_modes[vic];
3083 clock2 = hdmi_mode_alternate_clock(cea_mode);
3084 }
3085 }
3086
3087 if (!cea_mode)
3088 continue;
3089
3090 clock1 = cea_mode->clock;
3091
3092 if (clock1 == clock2)
3093 continue;
3094
3095 if (mode->clock != clock1 && mode->clock != clock2)
3096 continue;
3097
3098 newmode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, cea_mode);
3099 if (!newmode)
3100 continue;
3101
3102 /* Carry over the stereo flags */
3103 newmode->flags |= mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_MASK;
3104
3105 /*
3106 * The current mode could be either variant. Make
3107 * sure to pick the "other" clock for the new mode.
3108 */
3109 if (mode->clock != clock1)
3110 newmode->clock = clock1;
3111 else
3112 newmode->clock = clock2;
3113
3114 list_add_tail(&newmode->head, &list);
3115 }
3116
3117 list_for_each_entry_safe(mode, tmp, &list, head) {
3118 list_del(&mode->head);
3119 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, mode);
3120 modes++;
3121 }
3122
3123 return modes;
3124}

3126static u8 svd_to_vic(u8 svd)
3127{
3128 /* 0-6 bit vic, 7th bit native mode indicator */
3129 if ((svd >= 1 && svd <= 64) || (svd >= 129 && svd <= 192))
3130 return svd & 127;
3131
3132 return svd;
3133}

3135static struct drm_display_mode *
3136drm_display_mode_from_vic_index(struct drm_connector *connector,
3137 const u8 *video_db, u8 video_len,
3138 u8 video_index)
3139{
3140 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;

3161/*
3162 * do_y420vdb_modes - Parse YCBCR 420 only modes
3163 * @connector: connector corresponding to the HDMI sink
3164 * @svds: start of the data block of CEA YCBCR 420 VDB
3165 * @len: length of the CEA YCBCR 420 VDB
3166 *
3167 * Parse the CEA-861-F YCBCR 420 Video Data Block (Y420VDB)
3168 * which contains modes which can be supported in YCBCR 420
3169 * output format only.
3170 */
3171static int do_y420vdb_modes(struct drm_connector *connector,
3172 const u8 *svds, u8 svds_len)
3173{

3176 struct drm_display_info *info = &connector->display_info;
3177 struct drm_hdmi_info *hdmi = &info->hdmi;
3178

3184 continue;

3218static int
3219do_cea_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, const u8 *db, u8 len)
3220{
3221 int i, modes = 0;
3222 struct drm_hdmi_info *hdmi = &connector->display_info.hdmi;
3223
3224 for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
3225 struct drm_display_mode *mode;
3226 mode = drm_display_mode_from_vic_index(connector, db, len, i);
3227 if (mode) {
3228 /*
3229 * YCBCR420 capability block contains a bitmap which
3230 * gives the index of CEA modes from CEA VDB, which
3231 * can support YCBCR 420 sampling output also (apart
3232 * from RGB/YCBCR444 etc).
3233 * For example, if the bit 0 in bitmap is set,
3234 * first mode in VDB can support YCBCR420 output too.
3235 * Add YCBCR420 modes only if sink is HDMI 2.0 capable.
3236 */
3237 if (i < 64 && hdmi->y420_cmdb_map & (1ULL << i))
3238 drm_add_cmdb_modes(connector, db[i]);
3239
3240 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, mode);
3241 modes++;
3242 }
3243 }
3244
3245 return modes;

3371/*
3372 * do_hdmi_vsdb_modes - Parse the HDMI Vendor Specific data block
3373 * @connector: connector corresponding to the HDMI sink
3374 * @db: start of the CEA vendor specific block
3375 * @len: length of the CEA block payload, ie. one can access up to db[len]
3376 *
3377 * Parses the HDMI VSDB looking for modes to add to @connector. This function
3378 * also adds the stereo 3d modes when applicable.
3379 */
3380static int
3381do_hdmi_vsdb_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, const u8 *db, u8 len,
3382 const u8 *video_db, u8 video_len)
3383{
3384 int modes = 0, offset = 0, i, multi_present = 0, multi_len;
3385 u8 vic_len, hdmi_3d_len = 0;
3386 u16 mask;
3387 u16 structure_all;
3388
3389 if (len < 8)
3390 goto out;
3391
3392 /* no HDMI_Video_Present */
3393 if (!(db[8] & (1 << 5)))
3394 goto out;
3395
3396 /* Latency_Fields_Present */
3397 if (db[8] & (1 << 7))
3398 offset += 2;
3399
3400 /* I_Latency_Fields_Present */
3401 if (db[8] & (1 << 6))
3402 offset += 2;
3403
3404 /* the declared length is not long enough for the 2 first bytes
3405 * of additional video format capabilities */
3406 if (len < (8 + offset + 2))
3407 goto out;
3408
3409 /* 3D_Present */
3410 offset++;
3411 if (db[8 + offset] & (1 << 7)) {
3412 modes += add_hdmi_mandatory_stereo_modes(connector);
3413
3414 /* 3D_Multi_present */
3415 multi_present = (db[8 + offset] & 0x60) >> 5;
3416 }
3417
3418 offset++;
3419 vic_len = db[8 + offset] >> 5;
3420 hdmi_3d_len = db[8 + offset] & 0x1f;
3421
3422 for (i = 0; i < vic_len && len >= (9 + offset + i); i++) {
3423 u8 vic;
3424
3425 vic = db[9 + offset + i];
3426 modes += add_hdmi_mode(connector, vic);
3427 }
3428 offset += 1 + vic_len;
3429
3430 if (multi_present == 1)
3431 multi_len = 2;
3432 else if (multi_present == 2)
3433 multi_len = 4;
3434 else
3435 multi_len = 0;
3436
3437 if (len < (8 + offset + hdmi_3d_len - 1))
3438 goto out;
3439
3440 if (hdmi_3d_len < multi_len)
3441 goto out;
3442
3443 if (multi_present == 1 || multi_present == 2) {
3444 /* 3D_Structure_ALL */
3445 structure_all = (db[8 + offset] << 8) | db[9 + offset];
3446
3447 /* check if 3D_MASK is present */
3448 if (multi_present == 2)
3449 mask = (db[10 + offset] << 8) | db[11 + offset];
3450 else
3451 mask = 0xffff;
3452
3453 for (i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
3454 if (mask & (1 << i))
3455 modes += add_3d_struct_modes(connector,
3456 structure_all,
3457 video_db,
3458 video_len, i);
3459 }
3460 }
3461
3462 offset += multi_len;
3463
3464 for (i = 0; i < (hdmi_3d_len - multi_len); i++) {
3465 int vic_index;
3466 struct drm_display_mode *newmode = NULL;
3467 unsigned int newflag = 0;
3468 bool detail_present;
3469
3470 detail_present = ((db[8 + offset + i] & 0x0f) > 7);
3471
3472 if (detail_present && (i + 1 == hdmi_3d_len - multi_len))
3473 break;
3474
3475 /* 2D_VIC_order_X */
3476 vic_index = db[8 + offset + i] >> 4;
3477
3478 /* 3D_Structure_X */
3479 switch (db[8 + offset + i] & 0x0f) {
3480 case 0:
3481 newflag = DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_FRAME_PACKING;
3482 break;
3483 case 6:
3484 newflag = DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_TOP_AND_BOTTOM;
3485 break;
3486 case 8:
3487 /* 3D_Detail_X */
3488 if ((db[9 + offset + i] >> 4) == 1)
3489 newflag = DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_SIDE_BY_SIDE_HALF;
3490 break;
3491 }
3492
3493 if (newflag != 0) {
3494 newmode = drm_display_mode_from_vic_index(connector,
3495 video_db,
3496 video_len,
3497 vic_index);
3498
3499 if (newmode) {
3500 newmode->flags |= newflag;
3501 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
3502 modes++;
3503 }
3504 }
3505
3506 if (detail_present)
3507 i++;
3508 }
3509
3510out:
3511 return modes;
3512}

3609#define for_each_cea_db(cea, i, start, end) \
3610 for ((i) = (start); (i) < (end) && (i) + cea_db_payload_len(&(cea)[(i)]) < (end); (i) += cea_db_payload_len(&(cea)[(i)]) + 1)
3611
3612static void drm_parse_y420cmdb_bitmap(struct drm_connector *connector,
3613 const u8 *db)
3614{
3615 struct drm_display_info *info = &connector->display_info;
3616 struct drm_hdmi_info *hdmi = &info->hdmi;
3617 u8 map_len = cea_db_payload_len(db) - 1;
3618 u8 count;
3619 u64 map = 0;
3620
3621 if (map_len == 0) {
3622 /* All CEA modes support ycbcr420 sampling also.*/
3623 hdmi->y420_cmdb_map = U64_MAX;
3624 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_YCRCB420;
3625 return;
3626 }
3627
3628 /*
3629 * This map indicates which of the existing CEA block modes
3630 * from VDB can support YCBCR420 output too. So if bit=0 is
3631 * set, first mode from VDB can support YCBCR420 output too.
3632 * We will parse and keep this map, before parsing VDB itself
3633 * to avoid going through the same block again and again.
3634 *
3635 * Spec is not clear about max possible size of this block.
3636 * Clamping max bitmap block size at 8 bytes. Every byte can
3637 * address 8 CEA modes, in this way this map can address
3638 * 8*8 = first 64 SVDs.
3639 */
3640 if (WARN_ON_ONCE(map_len > 8))
3641 map_len = 8;
3642
3643 for (count = 0; count < map_len; count++)
3644 map |= (u64)db[2 + count] << (8 * count);
3645
3646 if (map)
3647 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_YCRCB420;
3648
3649 hdmi->y420_cmdb_map = map;
3650}
3651
3652static int
3653add_cea_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid)
3654{
3655 const u8 *cea = drm_find_cea_extension(edid);
3656 const u8 *db, *hdmi = NULL, *video = NULL;
3657 u8 dbl, hdmi_len, video_len = 0;
3658 int modes = 0;
3659
3660 if (cea && cea_revision(cea) >= 3) {
3661 int i, start, end;
3662
3663 if (cea_db_offsets(cea, &start, &end))
3664 return 0;
3665
3666 for_each_cea_db(cea, i, start, end) {
3667 db = &cea[i];
3668 dbl = cea_db_payload_len(db);
3669
3670 if (cea_db_tag(db) == VIDEO_BLOCK) {
3671 video = db + 1;
3672 video_len = dbl;
3673 modes += do_cea_modes(connector, video, dbl);
3674 } else if (cea_db_is_hdmi_vsdb(db)) {
3675 hdmi = db;
3676 hdmi_len = dbl;
3677 } else if (cea_db_is_y420vdb(db)) {
3678 const u8 *vdb420 = &db[2];
3679
3680 /* Add 4:2:0(only) modes present in EDID */
3681 modes += do_y420vdb_modes(connector,
3682 vdb420,
3683 dbl - 1);
3684 }
3685 }
3686 }
3687
3688 /*
3689 * We parse the HDMI VSDB after having added the cea modes as we will
3690 * be patching their flags when the sink supports stereo 3D.
3691 */
3692 if (hdmi)
3693 modes += do_hdmi_vsdb_modes(connector, hdmi, hdmi_len, video,
3694 video_len);
3695
3696 return modes;
3697}
3698
3699static void fixup_detailed_cea_mode_clock(struct drm_display_mode *mode)
3700{
3701 const struct drm_display_mode *cea_mode;
3702 int clock1, clock2, clock;
3703 u8 vic;
3704 const char *type;
3705
3706 /*
3707 * allow 5kHz clock difference either way to account for
3708 * the 10kHz clock resolution limit of detailed timings.
3709 */
3710 vic = drm_match_cea_mode_clock_tolerance(mode, 5);
3711 if (drm_valid_cea_vic(vic)) {
3712 type = "CEA";
3713 cea_mode = &edid_cea_modes[vic];
3714 clock1 = cea_mode->clock;
3715 clock2 = cea_mode_alternate_clock(cea_mode);
3716 } else {
3717 vic = drm_match_hdmi_mode_clock_tolerance(mode, 5);
3718 if (drm_valid_hdmi_vic(vic)) {
3719 type = "HDMI";
3720 cea_mode = &edid_4k_modes[vic];
3721 clock1 = cea_mode->clock;
3722 clock2 = hdmi_mode_alternate_clock(cea_mode);
3723 } else {
3724 return;
3725 }
3726 }
3727
3728 /* pick whichever is closest */
3729 if (abs(mode->clock - clock1) < abs(mode->clock - clock2))
3730 clock = clock1;
3731 else
3732 clock = clock2;
3733
3734 if (mode->clock == clock)
3735 return;
3736
3737 DRM_DEBUG("detailed mode matches %s VIC %d, adjusting clock %d -> %d\n",
3738 type, vic, mode->clock, clock);
3739 mode->clock = clock;
3740}
3741
3742static void
3743drm_parse_hdmi_vsdb_audio(struct drm_connector *connector, const u8 *db)
3744{
3745 u8 len = cea_db_payload_len(db);
3746
3747 if (len >= 6)
3748 connector->eld[5] |= (db[6] >> 7) << 1; /* Supports_AI */
3749 if (len >= 8) {
3750 connector->latency_present[0] = db[8] >> 7;
3751 connector->latency_present[1] = (db[8] >> 6) & 1;
3752 }
3753 if (len >= 9)
3754 connector->video_latency[0] = db[9];
3755 if (len >= 10)
3756 connector->audio_latency[0] = db[10];
3757 if (len >= 11)
3758 connector->video_latency[1] = db[11];
3759 if (len >= 12)
3760 connector->audio_latency[1] = db[12];
3761
3762 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("HDMI: latency present %d %d, "
3763 "video latency %d %d, "
3764 "audio latency %d %d\n",
3765 connector->latency_present[0],
3766 connector->latency_present[1],
3767 connector->video_latency[0],
3768 connector->video_latency[1],
3769 connector->audio_latency[0],
3770 connector->audio_latency[1]);
3771}

3773static void
3774monitor_name(struct detailed_timing *t, void *data)
3775{
3776 if (t->data.other_data.type == EDID_DETAIL_MONITOR_NAME)
3777 *(u8 **)data = t->data.other_data.data.str.str;
3778}
3779
3780static int get_monitor_name(struct edid *edid, char name[13])
3781{
3782 char *edid_name = NULL;
3783 int mnl;
3784
3785 if (!edid || !name)
3786 return 0;
3787
3788 drm_for_each_detailed_block((u8 *)edid, monitor_name, &edid_name);
3789 for (mnl = 0; edid_name && mnl < 13; mnl++) {
3790 if (edid_name[mnl] == 0x0a)
3791 break;
3792
3793 name[mnl] = edid_name[mnl];
3794 }
3795
3796 return mnl;
3797}

3799/**
3800 * drm_edid_get_monitor_name - fetch the monitor name from the edid
3801 * @edid: monitor EDID information
3802 * @name: pointer to a character array to hold the name of the monitor
3803 * @bufsize: The size of the name buffer (should be at least 14 chars.)
3804 *
3805 */
3806void drm_edid_get_monitor_name(struct edid *edid, char *name, int bufsize)
3807{
3808 int name_length;
3809 char buf[13];
3810
3811 if (bufsize <= 0)
3812 return;
3813
3814 name_length = min(get_monitor_name(edid, buf), bufsize - 1);
3815 memcpy(name, buf, name_length);
3816 name[name_length] = '\0';
3817}

3820/**
3821 * drm_edid_to_eld - build ELD from EDID
3822 * @connector: connector corresponding to the HDMI/DP sink
3823 * @edid: EDID to parse
3824 *
3825 * Fill the ELD (EDID-Like Data) buffer for passing to the audio driver. The
3826 * HDCP and Port_ID ELD fields are left for the graphics driver to fill in.
3827 */
3828void drm_edid_to_eld(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid)
3829{
3830 uint8_t *eld = connector->eld;
3831 u8 *cea;
3832 u8 *db;
3833 int total_sad_count = 0;
3834 int mnl;
3835 int dbl;
3836
3837 memset(eld, 0, sizeof(connector->eld));
3838
3839 connector->latency_present[0] = false;
3840 connector->latency_present[1] = false;
3841 connector->video_latency[0] = 0;
3842 connector->audio_latency[0] = 0;
3843 connector->video_latency[1] = 0;
3844 connector->audio_latency[1] = 0;
3845
3846 if (!edid)
3847 return;
3848
3849 cea = drm_find_cea_extension(edid);
3850 if (!cea) {
3851 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ELD: no CEA Extension found\n");
3852 return;
3853 }
3854
3855 mnl = get_monitor_name(edid, eld + 20);
3856
3857 eld[4] = (cea[1] << 5) | mnl;
3858 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ELD monitor %s\n", eld + 20);
3859
3860 eld[0] = 2 << 3; /* ELD version: 2 */
3861
3862 eld[16] = edid->mfg_id[0];
3863 eld[17] = edid->mfg_id[1];
3864 eld[18] = edid->prod_code[0];
3865 eld[19] = edid->prod_code[1];
3866
3867 if (cea_revision(cea) >= 3) {
3868 int i, start, end;
3869
3870 if (cea_db_offsets(cea, &start, &end)) {
3871 start = 0;
3872 end = 0;
3873 }
3874
3875 for_each_cea_db(cea, i, start, end) {
3876 db = &cea[i];
3877 dbl = cea_db_payload_len(db);
3878
3879 switch (cea_db_tag(db)) {
3880 int sad_count;
3881
3882 case AUDIO_BLOCK:
3883 /* Audio Data Block, contains SADs */
3884 sad_count = min(dbl / 3, 15 - total_sad_count);
3885 if (sad_count >= 1)
3886 memcpy(eld + 20 + mnl + total_sad_count * 3,
3887 &db[1], sad_count * 3);
3888 total_sad_count += sad_count;
3889 break;
3890 case SPEAKER_BLOCK:
3891 /* Speaker Allocation Data Block */
3892 if (dbl >= 1)
3893 eld[7] = db[1];
3894 break;
3895 case VENDOR_BLOCK:
3896 /* HDMI Vendor-Specific Data Block */
3897 if (cea_db_is_hdmi_vsdb(db))
3898 drm_parse_hdmi_vsdb_audio(connector, db);
3899 break;
3900 default:
3901 break;
3902 }
3903 }
3904 }
3905 eld[5] |= total_sad_count << 4;
3906
3907 if (connector->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_DisplayPort ||
3908 connector->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_eDP)
3909 eld[DRM_ELD_SAD_COUNT_CONN_TYPE] |= DRM_ELD_CONN_TYPE_DP;
3910 else
3911 eld[DRM_ELD_SAD_COUNT_CONN_TYPE] |= DRM_ELD_CONN_TYPE_HDMI;
3912
3913 eld[DRM_ELD_BASELINE_ELD_LEN] =
3914 DIV_ROUND_UP(drm_eld_calc_baseline_block_size(eld), 4);
3915
3916 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ELD size %d, SAD count %d\n",
3917 drm_eld_size(eld), total_sad_count);
3918}
3919EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_edid_to_eld);
3920
3921/**
3922 * drm_edid_to_sad - extracts SADs from EDID
3923 * @edid: EDID to parse
3924 * @sads: pointer that will be set to the extracted SADs
3925 *
3926 * Looks for CEA EDID block and extracts SADs (Short Audio Descriptors) from it.
3927 *
3928 * Note: The returned pointer needs to be freed using kfree().
3929 *
3930 * Return: The number of found SADs or negative number on error.
3931 */
3932int drm_edid_to_sad(struct edid *edid, struct cea_sad **sads)
3933{
3934 int count = 0;
3935 int i, start, end, dbl;
3936 u8 *cea;
3937
3938 cea = drm_find_cea_extension(edid);
3939 if (!cea) {
3940 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SAD: no CEA Extension found\n");
3941 return -ENOENT;
3942 }
3943
3944 if (cea_revision(cea) < 3) {
3945 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SAD: wrong CEA revision\n");
3946 return -ENOTSUPP;
3947 }
3948
3949 if (cea_db_offsets(cea, &start, &end)) {
3950 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SAD: invalid data block offsets\n");
3951 return -EPROTO;
3952 }
3953
3954 for_each_cea_db(cea, i, start, end) {
3955 u8 *db = &cea[i];
3956
3957 if (cea_db_tag(db) == AUDIO_BLOCK) {
3958 int j;
3959 dbl = cea_db_payload_len(db);
3960
3961 count = dbl / 3; /* SAD is 3B */
3962 *sads = kcalloc(count, sizeof(**sads), GFP_KERNEL);
3963 if (!*sads)
3964 return -ENOMEM;
3965 for (j = 0; j < count; j++) {
3966 u8 *sad = &db[1 + j * 3];
3967
3968 (*sads)[j].format = (sad[0] & 0x78) >> 3;
3969 (*sads)[j].channels = sad[0] & 0x7;
3970 (*sads)[j].freq = sad[1] & 0x7F;
3971 (*sads)[j].byte2 = sad[2];
3972 }
3973 break;
3974 }
3975 }
3976
3977 return count;
3978}
3979EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_edid_to_sad);

3981/**
3982 * drm_edid_to_speaker_allocation - extracts Speaker Allocation Data Blocks from EDID
3983 * @edid: EDID to parse
3984 * @sadb: pointer to the speaker block
3985 *
3986 * Looks for CEA EDID block and extracts the Speaker Allocation Data Block from it.
3987 *
3988 * Note: The returned pointer needs to be freed using kfree().
3989 *
3990 * Return: The number of found Speaker Allocation Blocks or negative number on
3991 * error.
3992 */
3993int drm_edid_to_speaker_allocation(struct edid *edid, u8 **sadb)
3994{
3995 int count = 0;
3996 int i, start, end, dbl;
3997 const u8 *cea;
3998
3999 cea = drm_find_cea_extension(edid);
4000 if (!cea) {
4001 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SAD: no CEA Extension found\n");
4002 return -ENOENT;
4003 }
4004
4005 if (cea_revision(cea) < 3) {
4006 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SAD: wrong CEA revision\n");
4007 return -ENOTSUPP;
4008 }
4009
4010 if (cea_db_offsets(cea, &start, &end)) {
4011 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("SAD: invalid data block offsets\n");
4012 return -EPROTO;
4013 }
4014
4015 for_each_cea_db(cea, i, start, end) {
4016 const u8 *db = &cea[i];
4017
4018 if (cea_db_tag(db) == SPEAKER_BLOCK) {
4019 dbl = cea_db_payload_len(db);
4020
4021 /* Speaker Allocation Data Block */

4023 *sadb = kmemdup(&db[1], dbl, GFP_KERNEL);
4024 if (!*sadb)
4025 return -ENOMEM;
4026 count = dbl;
4027 break;
4028 }
4029 }
4030 }
4031
4032 return count;
4033}

4036/**
4037 * drm_av_sync_delay - compute the HDMI/DP sink audio-video sync delay
4038 * @connector: connector associated with the HDMI/DP sink
4039 * @mode: the display mode
4040 *
4041 * Return: The HDMI/DP sink's audio-video sync delay in milliseconds or 0 if
4042 * the sink doesn't support audio or video.
4043 */
4044int drm_av_sync_delay(struct drm_connector *connector,
4045 const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
4046{
4047 int i = !!(mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE);
4048 int a, v;
4049
4050 if (!connector->latency_present[0])
4051 return 0;
4052 if (!connector->latency_present[1])
4053 i = 0;
4054
4055 a = connector->audio_latency[i];
4056 v = connector->video_latency[i];
4057
4058 /*
4059 * HDMI/DP sink doesn't support audio or video?
4060 */
4061 if (a == 255 || v == 255)
4062 return 0;
4063
4064 /*
4065 * Convert raw EDID values to millisecond.
4066 * Treat unknown latency as 0ms.
4067 */
4068 if (a)
4069 a = min(2 * (a - 1), 500);
4070 if (v)
4071 v = min(2 * (v - 1), 500);
4072
4073 return max(v - a, 0);
4074}
4075EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_av_sync_delay);

4077/**
4078 * drm_detect_hdmi_monitor - detect whether monitor is HDMI
4079 * @edid: monitor EDID information
4080 *
4081 * Parse the CEA extension according to CEA-861-B.
4082 *
4083 * Return: True if the monitor is HDMI, false if not or unknown.
4084 */
4085bool drm_detect_hdmi_monitor(struct edid *edid)
4086{
4087 u8 *edid_ext;
4088 int i;
4089 int start_offset, end_offset;
4090
4091 edid_ext = drm_find_cea_extension(edid);
4092 if (!edid_ext)
4093 return false;
4094
4095 if (cea_db_offsets(edid_ext, &start_offset, &end_offset))
4096 return false;
4097
4098 /*
4099 * Because HDMI identifier is in Vendor Specific Block,
4100 * search it from all data blocks of CEA extension.
4101 */
4102 for_each_cea_db(edid_ext, i, start_offset, end_offset) {
4103 if (cea_db_is_hdmi_vsdb(&edid_ext[i]))
4104 return true;
4105 }
4106
4107 return false;
4108}

4111/**
4112 * drm_detect_monitor_audio - check monitor audio capability
4113 * @edid: EDID block to scan
4114 *
4115 * Monitor should have CEA extension block.
4116 * If monitor has 'basic audio', but no CEA audio blocks, it's 'basic
4117 * audio' only. If there is any audio extension block and supported
4118 * audio format, assume at least 'basic audio' support, even if 'basic
4119 * audio' is not defined in EDID.
4120 *
4121 * Return: True if the monitor supports audio, false otherwise.
4122 */
4123bool drm_detect_monitor_audio(struct edid *edid)
4124{
4125 u8 *edid_ext;
4126 int i, j;
4127 bool has_audio = false;
4128 int start_offset, end_offset;
4129
4130 edid_ext = drm_find_cea_extension(edid);
4131 if (!edid_ext)
4132 goto end;
4133
4134 has_audio = ((edid_ext[3] & EDID_BASIC_AUDIO) != 0);
4135
4136 if (has_audio) {
4137 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Monitor has basic audio support\n");
4138 goto end;
4139 }
4140
4141 if (cea_db_offsets(edid_ext, &start_offset, &end_offset))
4142 goto end;
4143
4144 for_each_cea_db(edid_ext, i, start_offset, end_offset) {
4145 if (cea_db_tag(&edid_ext[i]) == AUDIO_BLOCK) {
4146 has_audio = true;
4147 for (j = 1; j < cea_db_payload_len(&edid_ext[i]) + 1; j += 3)
4148 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("CEA audio format %d\n",
4149 (edid_ext[i + j] >> 3) & 0xf);
4150 goto end;
4151 }
4152 }
4153end:
4154 return has_audio;
4155}
4156EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_detect_monitor_audio);

4158/**
4159 * drm_rgb_quant_range_selectable - is RGB quantization range selectable?
4160 * @edid: EDID block to scan
4161 *
4162 * Check whether the monitor reports the RGB quantization range selection
4163 * as supported. The AVI infoframe can then be used to inform the monitor
4164 * which quantization range (full or limited) is used.
4165 *

4213static void drm_parse_ycbcr420_deep_color_info(struct drm_connector *connector,
4214 const u8 *db)
