4222
4223static void drm_parse_hdmi_forum_vsdb(struct drm_connector *connector,
4224 const u8 *hf_vsdb)
4225{
4226 struct drm_display_info *display = &connector->display_info;
4227 struct drm_hdmi_info *hdmi = &display->hdmi;
4228
4229 if (hf_vsdb[6] & 0x80) {
4230 hdmi->scdc.supported = true;
4231 if (hf_vsdb[6] & 0x40)
4232 hdmi->scdc.read_request = true;
4233 }
4234
4235 /*
4236 * All HDMI 2.0 monitors must support scrambling at rates > 340 MHz.
4237 * And as per the spec, three factors confirm this:
4238 * * Availability of a HF-VSDB block in EDID (check)
4239 * * Non zero Max_TMDS_Char_Rate filed in HF-VSDB (let's check)
4240 * * SCDC support available (let's check)
4241 * Lets check it out.
4242 */
4243
4244 if (hf_vsdb[5]) {
4245 /* max clock is 5000 KHz times block value */
4246 u32 max_tmds_clock = hf_vsdb[5] * 5000;
4247 struct drm_scdc *scdc = &hdmi->scdc;
4248
4249 if (max_tmds_clock > 340000) {
4250 display->max_tmds_clock = max_tmds_clock;
4251 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("HF-VSDB: max TMDS clock %d kHz\n",
4252 display->max_tmds_clock);
4253 }
4254
4255 if (scdc->supported) {
4256 scdc->scrambling.supported = true;
4257
4258 /* Few sinks support scrambling for cloks < 340M */
4259 if ((hf_vsdb[6] & 0x8))
4260 scdc->scrambling.low_rates = true;
4261 }
4262 }
4263
4264 drm_parse_ycbcr420_deep_color_info(connector, hf_vsdb);
4265}
4266
4267static void drm_parse_hdmi_deep_color_info(struct drm_connector *connector,
4268 const u8 *hdmi)
4269{
4270 struct drm_display_info *info = &connector->display_info;
4271 unsigned int dc_bpc = 0;
4272
4273 /* HDMI supports at least 8 bpc */
4274 info->bpc = 8;
4275
4276 if (cea_db_payload_len(hdmi) < 6)
4277 return;
4278
4279 if (hdmi[6] & DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_30) {
4280 dc_bpc = 10;
4281 info->edid_hdmi_dc_modes |= DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_30;
4282 DRM_DEBUG("%s: HDMI sink does deep color 30.\n",
4283 connector->name);
4284 }
4285
4286 if (hdmi[6] & DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_36) {
4287 dc_bpc = 12;
4288 info->edid_hdmi_dc_modes |= DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_36;
4289 DRM_DEBUG("%s: HDMI sink does deep color 36.\n",
4290 connector->name);
4291 }
4292
4293 if (hdmi[6] & DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_48) {
4294 dc_bpc = 16;
4295 info->edid_hdmi_dc_modes |= DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_48;
4296 DRM_DEBUG("%s: HDMI sink does deep color 48.\n",
4297 connector->name);
4298 }
4299
4300 if (dc_bpc == 0) {
4301 DRM_DEBUG("%s: No deep color support on this HDMI sink.\n",
4302 connector->name);
4303 return;
4304 }
4305
4306 DRM_DEBUG("%s: Assigning HDMI sink color depth as %d bpc.\n",
4307 connector->name, dc_bpc);
4308 info->bpc = dc_bpc;
4309
4310 /*
4311 * Deep color support mandates RGB444 support for all video
4312 * modes and forbids YCRCB422 support for all video modes per
4313 * HDMI 1.3 spec.
4314 */
4315 info->color_formats = DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_RGB444;
4316
4317 /* YCRCB444 is optional according to spec. */
4318 if (hdmi[6] & DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_Y444) {
4319 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_YCRCB444;
4320 DRM_DEBUG("%s: HDMI sink does YCRCB444 in deep color.\n",
4321 connector->name);
4322 }
4323
4324 /*
4325 * Spec says that if any deep color mode is supported at all,
4326 * then deep color 36 bit must be supported.
4327 */
4328 if (!(hdmi[6] & DRM_EDID_HDMI_DC_36)) {
4329 DRM_DEBUG("%s: HDMI sink should do DC_36, but does not!\n",
4330 connector->name);
4331 }
4332}
4333
4334static void
4335drm_parse_hdmi_vsdb_video(struct drm_connector *connector, const u8 *db)
4336{
4337 struct drm_display_info *info = &connector->display_info;
4338 u8 len = cea_db_payload_len(db);
4339
4340 if (len >= 6)
4341 info->dvi_dual = db[6] & 1;
4342 if (len >= 7)
4343 info->max_tmds_clock = db[7] * 5000;
4344
4345 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("HDMI: DVI dual %d, "
4346 "max TMDS clock %d kHz\n",
4347 info->dvi_dual,
4348 info->max_tmds_clock);
4349
4350 drm_parse_hdmi_deep_color_info(connector, db);
4351}
4352
4353static void drm_parse_cea_ext(struct drm_connector *connector,
4354 struct edid *edid)
4355{
4356 struct drm_display_info *info = &connector->display_info;
4357 const u8 *edid_ext;
4358 int i, start, end;
4359
4360 edid_ext = drm_find_cea_extension(edid);
4361 if (!edid_ext)
4362 return;
4363
4364 info->cea_rev = edid_ext[1];
4365
4366 /* The existence of a CEA block should imply RGB support */
4367 info->color_formats = DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_RGB444;
4368 if (edid_ext[3] & EDID_CEA_YCRCB444)
4369 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_YCRCB444;
4370 if (edid_ext[3] & EDID_CEA_YCRCB422)
4371 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_YCRCB422;
4372
4373 if (cea_db_offsets(edid_ext, &start, &end))
4374 return;
4375
4376 for_each_cea_db(edid_ext, i, start, end) {
4377 const u8 *db = &edid_ext[i];
4378
4379 if (cea_db_is_hdmi_vsdb(db))
4380 drm_parse_hdmi_vsdb_video(connector, db);
4381 if (cea_db_is_hdmi_forum_vsdb(db))
4382 drm_parse_hdmi_forum_vsdb(connector, db);
4383 if (cea_db_is_y420cmdb(db))
4384 drm_parse_y420cmdb_bitmap(connector, db);
4385 }
4386}
4387
4388static void drm_add_display_info(struct drm_connector *connector,
4389 struct edid *edid)
4390{
4391 struct drm_display_info *info = &connector->display_info;
4392
4393 info->width_mm = edid->width_cm * 10;
4394 info->height_mm = edid->height_cm * 10;
4395
4396 /* driver figures it out in this case */
4397 info->bpc = 0;
4398 info->color_formats = 0;
4399 info->cea_rev = 0;
4400 info->max_tmds_clock = 0;
4401 info->dvi_dual = false;
4402
4403 if (edid->revision < 3)
4404 return;
4405
4406 if (!(edid->input & DRM_EDID_INPUT_DIGITAL))
4407 return;
4408
4409 drm_parse_cea_ext(connector, edid);
4410
4411 /*
4412 * Digital sink with "DFP 1.x compliant TMDS" according to EDID 1.3?
4413 *
4414 * For such displays, the DFP spec 1.0, section 3.10 "EDID support"
4415 * tells us to assume 8 bpc color depth if the EDID doesn't have
4416 * extensions which tell otherwise.
4417 */
4418 if ((info->bpc == 0) && (edid->revision < 4) &&
4419 (edid->input & DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_TYPE_DVI)) {
4420 info->bpc = 8;
4421 DRM_DEBUG("%s: Assigning DFP sink color depth as %d bpc.\n",
4422 connector->name, info->bpc);
4423 }
4424
4425 /* Only defined for 1.4 with digital displays */
4426 if (edid->revision < 4)
4427 return;
4428
4429 switch (edid->input & DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_MASK) {
4430 case DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_6:
4431 info->bpc = 6;
4432 break;
4433 case DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_8:
4434 info->bpc = 8;
4435 break;
4436 case DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_10:
4437 info->bpc = 10;
4438 break;
4439 case DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_12:
4440 info->bpc = 12;
4441 break;
4442 case DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_14:
4443 info->bpc = 14;
4444 break;
4445 case DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_16:
4446 info->bpc = 16;
4447 break;
4448 case DRM_EDID_DIGITAL_DEPTH_UNDEF:
4449 default:
4450 info->bpc = 0;
4451 break;
4452 }
4453
4454 DRM_DEBUG("%s: Assigning EDID-1.4 digital sink color depth as %d bpc.\n",
4455 connector->name, info->bpc);
4456
4457 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_RGB444;
4458 if (edid->features & DRM_EDID_FEATURE_RGB_YCRCB444)
4459 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_YCRCB444;
4460 if (edid->features & DRM_EDID_FEATURE_RGB_YCRCB422)
4461 info->color_formats |= DRM_COLOR_FORMAT_YCRCB422;
4462}
4463
4464static int validate_displayid(u8 *displayid, int length, int idx)
4465{
4466 int i;
4467 u8 csum = 0;
4468 struct displayid_hdr *base;
4469
4470 base = (struct displayid_hdr *)&displayid[idx];
4471
4472 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("base revision 0x%x, length %d, %d %d\n",
4473 base->rev, base->bytes, base->prod_id, base->ext_count);
4474
4475 if (base->bytes + 5 > length - idx)
4476 return -EINVAL;
4477 for (i = idx; i <= base->bytes + 5; i++) {
4478 csum += displayid[i];
4479 }
4480 if (csum) {
4481 DRM_NOTE("DisplayID checksum invalid, remainder is %d\n", csum);
4482 return -EINVAL;
4483 }
4484 return 0;
4485}
4486
4487static struct drm_display_mode *drm_mode_displayid_detailed(struct drm_device *dev,
4488 struct displayid_detailed_timings_1 *timings)
4489{
4490 struct drm_display_mode *mode;
4491 unsigned pixel_clock = (timings->pixel_clock[0] |
4492 (timings->pixel_clock[1] << 8) |
4493 (timings->pixel_clock[2] << 16));
4494 unsigned hactive = (timings->hactive[0] | timings->hactive[1] << 8) + 1;
4495 unsigned hblank = (timings->hblank[0] | timings->hblank[1] << 8) + 1;
4496 unsigned hsync = (timings->hsync[0] | (timings->hsync[1] & 0x7f) << 8) + 1;
4497 unsigned hsync_width = (timings->hsw[0] | timings->hsw[1] << 8) + 1;
4498 unsigned vactive = (timings->vactive[0] | timings->vactive[1] << 8) + 1;
4499 unsigned vblank = (timings->vblank[0] | timings->vblank[1] << 8) + 1;
4500 unsigned vsync = (timings->vsync[0] | (timings->vsync[1] & 0x7f) << 8) + 1;
4501 unsigned vsync_width = (timings->vsw[0] | timings->vsw[1] << 8) + 1;
4502 bool hsync_positive = (timings->hsync[1] >> 7) & 0x1;
4503 bool vsync_positive = (timings->vsync[1] >> 7) & 0x1;
4504 mode = drm_mode_create(dev);
4505 if (!mode)
4506 return NULL;
4507
4508 mode->clock = pixel_clock * 10;
4509 mode->hdisplay = hactive;
4510 mode->hsync_start = mode->hdisplay + hsync;
4511 mode->hsync_end = mode->hsync_start + hsync_width;
4512 mode->htotal = mode->hdisplay + hblank;
4513
4514 mode->vdisplay = vactive;
4515 mode->vsync_start = mode->vdisplay + vsync;
4516 mode->vsync_end = mode->vsync_start + vsync_width;
4517 mode->vtotal = mode->vdisplay + vblank;
4518
4519 mode->flags = 0;
4520 mode->flags |= hsync_positive ? DRM_MODE_FLAG_PHSYNC : DRM_MODE_FLAG_NHSYNC;
4521 mode->flags |= vsync_positive ? DRM_MODE_FLAG_PVSYNC : DRM_MODE_FLAG_NVSYNC;
4522 mode->type = DRM_MODE_TYPE_DRIVER;
4523
4524 if (timings->flags & 0x80)
4525 mode->type |= DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;
4526 mode->vrefresh = drm_mode_vrefresh(mode);
4527 drm_mode_set_name(mode);
4528
4529 return mode;
4530}
4531
4532static int add_displayid_detailed_1_modes(struct drm_connector *connector,
4533 struct displayid_block *block)
4534{
4535 struct displayid_detailed_timing_block *det = (struct displayid_detailed_timing_block *)block;
4536 int i;
4537 int num_timings;
4538 struct drm_display_mode *newmode;
4539 int num_modes = 0;
4540 /* blocks must be multiple of 20 bytes length */
4541 if (block->num_bytes % 20)
4542 return 0;
4543
4544 num_timings = block->num_bytes / 20;
4545 for (i = 0; i < num_timings; i++) {
4546 struct displayid_detailed_timings_1 *timings = &det->timings[i];
4547
4548 newmode = drm_mode_displayid_detailed(connector->dev, timings);
4549 if (!newmode)
4550 continue;
4551
4552 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, newmode);
4553 num_modes++;
4554 }
4555 return num_modes;
4556}
4557
4558static int add_displayid_detailed_modes(struct drm_connector *connector,
4559 struct edid *edid)
4560{
4561 u8 *displayid;
4562 int ret;
4563 int idx = 1;
4564 int length = EDID_LENGTH;
4565 struct displayid_block *block;
4566 int num_modes = 0;
4567
4568 displayid = drm_find_displayid_extension(edid);
4569 if (!displayid)
4570 return 0;
4571
4572 ret = validate_displayid(displayid, length, idx);
4573 if (ret)
4574 return 0;
4575
4576 idx += sizeof(struct displayid_hdr);
4577 while (block = (struct displayid_block *)&displayid[idx],
4578 idx + sizeof(struct displayid_block) <= length &&
4579 idx + sizeof(struct displayid_block) + block->num_bytes <= length &&
4580 block->num_bytes > 0) {
4581 idx += block->num_bytes + sizeof(struct displayid_block);
4582 switch (block->tag) {
4583 case DATA_BLOCK_TYPE_1_DETAILED_TIMING:
4584 num_modes += add_displayid_detailed_1_modes(connector, block);
4585 break;
4586 }
4587 }
4588 return num_modes;
4589}
4590
4591/**
4592 * drm_add_edid_modes - add modes from EDID data, if available
4593 * @connector: connector we're probing
4594 * @edid: EDID data
4595 *
4596 * Add the specified modes to the connector's mode list. Also fills out the
4597 * &drm_display_info structure in @connector with any information which can be
4598 * derived from the edid.
4599 *
4600 * Return: The number of modes added or 0 if we couldn't find any.
4601 */
4602int drm_add_edid_modes(struct drm_connector *connector, struct edid *edid)
4603{
4604 int num_modes = 0;
4605 u32 quirks;
4606
4607 if (edid == NULL) {
4608 return 0;
4609 }
4610 if (!drm_edid_is_valid(edid)) {
4611 dev_warn(connector->dev->dev, "%s: EDID invalid.\n",
4612 connector->name);
4613 return 0;
4614 }
4615
4616 quirks = edid_get_quirks(edid);
4617
4618 /*
4619 * CEA-861-F adds ycbcr capability map block, for HDMI 2.0 sinks.
4620 * To avoid multiple parsing of same block, lets parse that map
4621 * from sink info, before parsing CEA modes.
4622 */
4623 drm_add_display_info(connector, edid);
4624
4625 /*
4626 * EDID spec says modes should be preferred in this order:
4627 * - preferred detailed mode
4628 * - other detailed modes from base block
4629 * - detailed modes from extension blocks
4630 * - CVT 3-byte code modes
4631 * - standard timing codes
4632 * - established timing codes
4633 * - modes inferred from GTF or CVT range information
4634 *
4635 * We get this pretty much right.
4636 *
4637 * XXX order for additional mode types in extension blocks?
4638 */
4639 num_modes += add_detailed_modes(connector, edid, quirks);
4640 num_modes += add_cvt_modes(connector, edid);
4641 num_modes += add_standard_modes(connector, edid);
4642 num_modes += add_established_modes(connector, edid);
4643 num_modes += add_cea_modes(connector, edid);
4644 num_modes += add_alternate_cea_modes(connector, edid);
4645 num_modes += add_displayid_detailed_modes(connector, edid);
4646 if (edid->features & DRM_EDID_FEATURE_DEFAULT_GTF)
4647 num_modes += add_inferred_modes(connector, edid);
4648
4649 if (quirks & (EDID_QUIRK_PREFER_LARGE_60 | EDID_QUIRK_PREFER_LARGE_75))
4650 edid_fixup_preferred(connector, quirks);
4651
4652 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_6BPC)
4653 connector->display_info.bpc = 6;
4654
4655 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_8BPC)
4656 connector->display_info.bpc = 8;
4657
4658 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_10BPC)
4659 connector->display_info.bpc = 10;
4660
4661 if (quirks & EDID_QUIRK_FORCE_12BPC)
4662 connector->display_info.bpc = 12;
4663
4664 return num_modes;
4665}
4666EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_add_edid_modes);
4667
4668/**
4669 * drm_add_modes_noedid - add modes for the connectors without EDID
4670 * @connector: connector we're probing
4671 * @hdisplay: the horizontal display limit
4672 * @vdisplay: the vertical display limit
4673 *
4674 * Add the specified modes to the connector's mode list. Only when the
4675 * hdisplay/vdisplay is not beyond the given limit, it will be added.
4676 *
4677 * Return: The number of modes added or 0 if we couldn't find any.
4678 */
4679int drm_add_modes_noedid(struct drm_connector *connector,
4680 int hdisplay, int vdisplay)
4681{
4682 int i, count, num_modes = 0;
4683 struct drm_display_mode *mode;
4684 struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
4685
4686 count = ARRAY_SIZE(drm_dmt_modes);
4687 if (hdisplay < 0)
4688 hdisplay = 0;
4689 if (vdisplay < 0)
4690 vdisplay = 0;
4691
4692 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
4693 const struct drm_display_mode *ptr = &drm_dmt_modes[i];
4694 if (hdisplay && vdisplay) {
4695 /*
4696 * Only when two are valid, they will be used to check
4697 * whether the mode should be added to the mode list of
4698 * the connector.
4699 */
4700 if (ptr->hdisplay > hdisplay ||
4701 ptr->vdisplay > vdisplay)
4702 continue;
4703 }
4704 if (drm_mode_vrefresh(ptr) > 61)
4705 continue;
4706 mode = drm_mode_duplicate(dev, ptr);
4707 if (mode) {
4708 drm_mode_probed_add(connector, mode);
4709 num_modes++;
4710 }
4711 }
4712 return num_modes;
4713}
4714EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_add_modes_noedid);

4717 * drm_set_preferred_mode - Sets the preferred mode of a connector
4718 * @connector: connector whose mode list should be processed
4719 * @hpref: horizontal resolution of preferred mode
4720 * @vpref: vertical resolution of preferred mode
4721 *
4722 * Marks a mode as preferred if it matches the resolution specified by @hpref

4733 mode->type |= DRM_MODE_TYPE_PREFERRED;

4738/**
4739 * drm_hdmi_avi_infoframe_from_display_mode() - fill an HDMI AVI infoframe with
4740 * data from a DRM display mode
4741 * @frame: HDMI AVI infoframe
4742 * @mode: DRM display mode
4743 * @is_hdmi2_sink: Sink is HDMI 2.0 compliant
4744 *
4745 * Return: 0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
4746 */
4747int
4748drm_hdmi_avi_infoframe_from_display_mode(struct hdmi_avi_infoframe *frame,
4749 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
4750 bool is_hdmi2_sink)
4751{
4752 int err;
4753
4754 if (!frame || !mode)
4755 return -EINVAL;
4756
4757 err = hdmi_avi_infoframe_init(frame);
4758 if (err < 0)
4759 return err;
4760
4761 if (mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_DBLCLK)
4762 frame->pixel_repeat = 1;
4763
4764 frame->video_code = drm_match_cea_mode(mode);
4765
4766 /*
4767 * HDMI 1.4 VIC range: 1 <= VIC <= 64 (CEA-861-D) but
4768 * HDMI 2.0 VIC range: 1 <= VIC <= 107 (CEA-861-F). So we
4769 * have to make sure we dont break HDMI 1.4 sinks.
4770 */
4771 if (!is_hdmi2_sink && frame->video_code > 64)
4772 frame->video_code = 0;
4773
4774 /*
4775 * HDMI spec says if a mode is found in HDMI 1.4b 4K modes
4776 * we should send its VIC in vendor infoframes, else send the
4777 * VIC in AVI infoframes. Lets check if this mode is present in
4778 * HDMI 1.4b 4K modes
4779 */
4780 if (frame->video_code) {
4781 u8 vendor_if_vic = drm_match_hdmi_mode(mode);
4782 bool is_s3d = mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_MASK;
4783
4784 if (drm_valid_hdmi_vic(vendor_if_vic) && !is_s3d)
4785 frame->video_code = 0;
4786 }
4787
4788 frame->picture_aspect = HDMI_PICTURE_ASPECT_NONE;
4789
4790 /*
4791 * Populate picture aspect ratio from either
4792 * user input (if specified) or from the CEA mode list.
4793 */
4794 if (mode->picture_aspect_ratio == HDMI_PICTURE_ASPECT_4_3 ||
4795 mode->picture_aspect_ratio == HDMI_PICTURE_ASPECT_16_9)
4796 frame->picture_aspect = mode->picture_aspect_ratio;
4797 else if (frame->video_code > 0)
4798 frame->picture_aspect = drm_get_cea_aspect_ratio(
4799 frame->video_code);
4800
4801 frame->active_aspect = HDMI_ACTIVE_ASPECT_PICTURE;
4802 frame->scan_mode = HDMI_SCAN_MODE_UNDERSCAN;
4803
4804 return 0;
4805}
4806EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_hdmi_avi_infoframe_from_display_mode);
4807
4808/**
4809 * drm_hdmi_avi_infoframe_quant_range() - fill the HDMI AVI infoframe
4810 * quantization range information
4811 * @frame: HDMI AVI infoframe
4812 * @mode: DRM display mode
4813 * @rgb_quant_range: RGB quantization range (Q)
4814 * @rgb_quant_range_selectable: Sink support selectable RGB quantization range (QS)
4815 */
4816void
4817drm_hdmi_avi_infoframe_quant_range(struct hdmi_avi_infoframe *frame,
4818 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
4819 enum hdmi_quantization_range rgb_quant_range,
4820 bool rgb_quant_range_selectable,
4821 bool is_hdmi2_sink)
4822{
4823 /*
4824 * CEA-861:
4825 * "A Source shall not send a non-zero Q value that does not correspond
4826 * to the default RGB Quantization Range for the transmitted Picture
4827 * unless the Sink indicates support for the Q bit in a Video
4828 * Capabilities Data Block."
4829 *
4830 * HDMI 2.0 recommends sending non-zero Q when it does match the
4831 * default RGB quantization range for the mode, even when QS=0.
4832 */
4833 if (rgb_quant_range_selectable ||
4834 rgb_quant_range == drm_default_rgb_quant_range(mode))
4835 frame->quantization_range = rgb_quant_range;
4836 else
4837 frame->quantization_range = HDMI_QUANTIZATION_RANGE_DEFAULT;
4838
4839 /*
4840 * CEA-861-F:
4841 * "When transmitting any RGB colorimetry, the Source should set the
4842 * YQ-field to match the RGB Quantization Range being transmitted
4843 * (e.g., when Limited Range RGB, set YQ=0 or when Full Range RGB,
4844 * set YQ=1) and the Sink shall ignore the YQ-field."
4845 *
4846 * Unfortunate certain sinks (eg. VIZ Model 67/E261VA) get confused
4847 * by non-zero YQ when receiving RGB. There doesn't seem to be any
4848 * good way to tell which version of CEA-861 the sink supports, so
4849 * we limit non-zero YQ to HDMI 2.0 sinks only as HDMI 2.0 is based
4850 * on on CEA-861-F.
4851 */
4852 if (!is_hdmi2_sink ||
4853 rgb_quant_range == HDMI_QUANTIZATION_RANGE_LIMITED)
4854 frame->ycc_quantization_range =
4855 HDMI_YCC_QUANTIZATION_RANGE_LIMITED;
4856 else
4857 frame->ycc_quantization_range =
4858 HDMI_YCC_QUANTIZATION_RANGE_FULL;
4859}
4860EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_hdmi_avi_infoframe_quant_range);

4862static enum hdmi_3d_structure
4863s3d_structure_from_display_mode(const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
4864{
4865 u32 layout = mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_MASK;
4866
4867 switch (layout) {
4868 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_FRAME_PACKING:
4869 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_FRAME_PACKING;
4870 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_FIELD_ALTERNATIVE:
4871 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_FIELD_ALTERNATIVE;
4872 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_LINE_ALTERNATIVE:
4873 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_LINE_ALTERNATIVE;
4874 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_SIDE_BY_SIDE_FULL:
4875 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_SIDE_BY_SIDE_FULL;
4876 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_L_DEPTH:
4877 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_L_DEPTH;
4878 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_L_DEPTH_GFX_GFX_DEPTH:
4879 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_L_DEPTH_GFX_GFX_DEPTH;
4880 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_TOP_AND_BOTTOM:
4881 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_TOP_AND_BOTTOM;
4882 case DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_SIDE_BY_SIDE_HALF:
4883 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_SIDE_BY_SIDE_HALF;
4884 default:
4885 return HDMI_3D_STRUCTURE_INVALID;
4886 }
4887}
4888
4889/**
4890 * drm_hdmi_vendor_infoframe_from_display_mode() - fill an HDMI infoframe with
4891 * data from a DRM display mode
4892 * @frame: HDMI vendor infoframe
4893 * @mode: DRM display mode
4894 *
4895 * Note that there's is a need to send HDMI vendor infoframes only when using a
4896 * 4k or stereoscopic 3D mode. So when giving any other mode as input this
4897 * function will return -EINVAL, error that can be safely ignored.
4898 *
4899 * Return: 0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
4900 */
4901int
4902drm_hdmi_vendor_infoframe_from_display_mode(struct hdmi_vendor_infoframe *frame,
4903 const struct drm_display_mode *mode)
4904{
4905 int err;
4906 u32 s3d_flags;
4907 u8 vic;
4908
4909 if (!frame || !mode)
4910 return -EINVAL;
4911
4912 vic = drm_match_hdmi_mode(mode);
4913 s3d_flags = mode->flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_3D_MASK;
4914
4915 if (!vic && !s3d_flags)
4916 return -EINVAL;
4917
4918 if (vic && s3d_flags)
4919 return -EINVAL;
4920
4921 err = hdmi_vendor_infoframe_init(frame);
4922 if (err < 0)
4923 return err;
4924
4925 if (vic)
4926 frame->vic = vic;
4927 else
4928 frame->s3d_struct = s3d_structure_from_display_mode(mode);
4929
4930 return 0;
4931}
4932EXPORT_SYMBOL(drm_hdmi_vendor_infoframe_from_display_mode);

4934static int drm_parse_tiled_block(struct drm_connector *connector,
4935 struct displayid_block *block)
4936{
4937 struct displayid_tiled_block *tile = (struct displayid_tiled_block *)block;
4938 u16 w, h;
4939 u8 tile_v_loc, tile_h_loc;
4940 u8 num_v_tile, num_h_tile;
4941 struct drm_tile_group *tg;
4942
4943 w = tile->tile_size[0] | tile->tile_size[1] << 8;
4944 h = tile->tile_size[2] | tile->tile_size[3] << 8;
4945
4946 num_v_tile = (tile->topo[0] & 0xf) | (tile->topo[2] & 0x30);
4947 num_h_tile = (tile->topo[0] >> 4) | ((tile->topo[2] >> 2) & 0x30);
4948 tile_v_loc = (tile->topo[1] & 0xf) | ((tile->topo[2] & 0x3) << 4);
4949 tile_h_loc = (tile->topo[1] >> 4) | (((tile->topo[2] >> 2) & 0x3) << 4);
4950
4951 connector->has_tile = true;
4952 if (tile->tile_cap & 0x80)
4953 connector->tile_is_single_monitor = true;
4954
4955 connector->num_h_tile = num_h_tile + 1;
4956 connector->num_v_tile = num_v_tile + 1;
4957 connector->tile_h_loc = tile_h_loc;
4958 connector->tile_v_loc = tile_v_loc;
4959 connector->tile_h_size = w + 1;
4960 connector->tile_v_size = h + 1;
4961
4962 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("tile cap 0x%x\n", tile->tile_cap);
4963 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("tile_size %d x %d\n", w + 1, h + 1);
4964 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("topo num tiles %dx%d, location %dx%d\n",
4965 num_h_tile + 1, num_v_tile + 1, tile_h_loc, tile_v_loc);
4966 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("vend %c%c%c\n", tile->topology_id[0], tile->topology_id[1], tile->topology_id[2]);
4967
4968 tg = drm_mode_get_tile_group(connector->dev, tile->topology_id);
4969 if (!tg) {
4970 tg = drm_mode_create_tile_group(connector->dev, tile->topology_id);
4971 }
4972 if (!tg)
4973 return -ENOMEM;
4974
4975 if (connector->tile_group != tg) {
4976 /* if we haven't got a pointer,
4977 take the reference, drop ref to old tile group */
4978 if (connector->tile_group) {
4979 drm_mode_put_tile_group(connector->dev, connector->tile_group);
4980 }
4981 connector->tile_group = tg;
4982 } else
4983 /* if same tile group, then release the ref we just took. */
4984 drm_mode_put_tile_group(connector->dev, tg);
4985 return 0;
4986}
4987
4988static int drm_parse_display_id(struct drm_connector *connector,
4989 u8 *displayid, int length,
4990 bool is_edid_extension)
4991{
4992 /* if this is an EDID extension the first byte will be 0x70 */
4993 int idx = 0;
4994 struct displayid_block *block;
4995 int ret;
4996
4997 if (is_edid_extension)
4998 idx = 1;
4999
5000 ret = validate_displayid(displayid, length, idx);
5001 if (ret)
5002 return ret;
5003
5004 idx += sizeof(struct displayid_hdr);
5005 while (block = (struct displayid_block *)&displayid[idx],
5006 idx + sizeof(struct displayid_block) <= length &&
5007 idx + sizeof(struct displayid_block) + block->num_bytes <= length &&
5008 block->num_bytes > 0) {
5009 idx += block->num_bytes + sizeof(struct displayid_block);
5010 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("block id 0x%x, rev %d, len %d\n",
5011 block->tag, block->rev, block->num_bytes);
5012
5013 switch (block->tag) {
5014 case DATA_BLOCK_TILED_DISPLAY:
5015 ret = drm_parse_tiled_block(connector, block);
5016 if (ret)
5017 return ret;
5018 break;
5019 case DATA_BLOCK_TYPE_1_DETAILED_TIMING:
5020 /* handled in mode gathering code. */
5021 break;
5022 default:
5023 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("found DisplayID tag 0x%x, unhandled\n", block->tag);
5024 break;
5025 }
5026 }
5027 return 0;
5028}
5029
5030static void drm_get_displayid(struct drm_connector *connector,
5031 struct edid *edid)
5032{
5033 void *displayid = NULL;
5034 int ret;
5035 connector->has_tile = false;
5036 displayid = drm_find_displayid_extension(edid);
5037 if (!displayid) {
5038 /* drop reference to any tile group we had */
5039 goto out_drop_ref;
5040 }
5041
5042 ret = drm_parse_display_id(connector, displayid, EDID_LENGTH, true);
5043 if (ret < 0)
5044 goto out_drop_ref;
5045 if (!connector->has_tile)
5046 goto out_drop_ref;
5047 return;
5048out_drop_ref:
5049 if (connector->tile_group) {
5050 drm_mode_put_tile_group(connector->dev, connector->tile_group);
5051 connector->tile_group = NULL;
5052 }
5053 return;
5054}
